You want to talk about Oprah,
we can talk about Oprah.

02:40.458 --> 02:42.526
You know, Reg.

02:42.528 --> 02:44.493
There ain't nothing
to talk about.

02:44.495 --> 02:46.695
Don't go giving me
attitude, Reginald.

02:46.697 --> 02:48.130
- Reginald?
- Yeah.

02:48.132 --> 02:50.499
- What's that? You're my mama now.
- Your mama?

02:50.501 --> 02:53.636
- [BOTH LAUGHING]
- You're going to scold me? Huh?

02:53.638 --> 02:56.409
- You don't look anything like my mama.
- I'm sure of that.

03:00.112 --> 03:02.548
[RAP MUSIC PLAYING
ON CAR STEREO]

03:07.185 --> 03:08.720
[MUSIC STOPS]

03:12.958 --> 03:14.523
You need to go.

03:14.525 --> 03:15.592
- Go.
- Reg...

03:15.594 --> 03:17.461
Mariah, go!

03:17.463 --> 03:19.729
REGGIE: Go, okay.

03:19.731 --> 03:21.701
What's going on, tough guy?

03:22.233 --> 03:23.867
PICK: Mmm-hmm.

03:23.869 --> 03:26.939
[EXCLAIMS] That yours?

03:28.040 --> 03:30.540
'Cause I'd like
a little of that.

03:30.542 --> 03:32.742
Hey, if she's yours,
I got you, bro.

03:32.744 --> 03:34.143
I'll even help you out.

03:34.145 --> 03:36.847
Break you off a little something,
make her lay down for her man,

03:36.849 --> 03:39.683
if you know what I mean?
[LAUGHS]

03:39.685 --> 03:41.784
Hey, If not, that's sweet,
is all I'm saying, bro.

03:41.786 --> 03:43.986
Cause you know I got a sweet
tooth, ain't that right, Brick?

03:43.988 --> 03:45.689
- [MEN LAUGHING]
- Hey, where you going?

03:45.691 --> 03:48.925
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

03:48.927 --> 03:51.096
Reggie, what you been
up to, man? Where you been at?

03:51.929 --> 03:53.698
- School.
- School?

03:54.500 --> 03:55.898
[CHUCKLES]

03:55.900 --> 03:58.034
What, you play ball now?

03:58.036 --> 04:00.070
Yeah, I ain't think
he was a baller.

04:00.072 --> 04:02.708
So why you do it, dawg? Why you
buy into all this school shit?

04:03.674 --> 04:04.808
How old are you now?

04:04.810 --> 04:06.742
- Sixteen.
- Sixteen.

04:06.744 --> 04:07.978
- Where your ride at?
- Don't have one.

04:07.980 --> 04:10.850
That's right. Cause you're
in school all the damn time.

04:11.716 --> 04:12.883
You see that?

04:12.885 --> 04:16.719
You ain't going to get that
playing their game, dawg.

04:16.721 --> 04:19.154
No, what you going to get
is a bunch of nickels and dimes

04:19.156 --> 04:20.690
and cheap ass talk
about success.

04:20.692 --> 04:24.897
But, nickels and dimes they don't get you
the ride. They don't get you the girl.

04:26.130 --> 04:27.933
And it damned sure,
ain't get you this.

04:28.767 --> 04:30.834
See this right here, baby?

04:30.836 --> 04:32.736
This is what
it's all about, dawg.

04:32.738 --> 04:34.173
This is where
you live, dawg.

04:36.041 --> 04:37.474
But you're smart,
Reggie.

04:37.476 --> 04:41.745
You get started and you will be
flushed overnight. I guarantee it.

04:41.747 --> 04:43.712
- I'm good, all right?
- Reggie.

04:43.714 --> 04:45.183
Reggie, Reggie, Reggie.

04:46.250 --> 04:48.053
What's up?
Why you being so cold?

04:49.221 --> 04:51.724
Oh! I know
what this is about.

04:52.156 --> 04:53.289
Your brother.

04:53.291 --> 04:54.791
Look, man,
I loved Chill Will too,

04:54.793 --> 04:56.025
but he wasn't
as smart as you.

04:56.027 --> 04:58.727
And that's why
that happened.

04:58.729 --> 05:00.697
He made
the big mistake, right?

05:00.699 --> 05:03.069
He stopped selling
and he started using.

05:04.135 --> 05:05.835
But, you're smarter
than that, kid.

05:05.837 --> 05:09.339
You're smart enough to make
this money and stay clean.

05:09.341 --> 05:11.808
Money to buy your little bit
of sweet some pretty clothes.

05:11.810 --> 05:13.976
- Money to put your mom in a new...
- I'm good, all right?

05:13.978 --> 05:15.277
Hey, where you going?

05:15.279 --> 05:17.012
I really don't think
you hear me.

05:17.014 --> 05:18.882
This is it
right here, bro.

05:18.884 --> 05:20.686
This is what
it's all about.

05:21.286 --> 05:22.788
Matter of fact,

05:23.354 --> 05:25.056
watch this. Yo!

05:25.990 --> 05:27.627
Wanna make a dollar?

05:29.026 --> 05:32.061
Yeah, come over here and make
you some money, dawg.

05:32.063 --> 05:33.164
[BRICK SPEAKS SPANISH]

05:35.366 --> 05:37.068
PICK: Come on,
man. Move.

05:38.236 --> 05:40.070
Come on, dawg.

05:40.072 --> 05:41.740
Watch this, bro.

05:44.642 --> 05:46.209
- Hop on one leg.
- [BRICK CHUCKLING]

05:46.211 --> 05:48.712
[BRICK SPEAKS SPANISH]

05:48.714 --> 05:49.846
[PICK AND BRICK LAUGHING]

05:49.848 --> 05:51.614
You see
what I'm talking about?

05:51.616 --> 05:53.383
Yeah, there you go.
You earned it.

05:53.385 --> 05:54.750
[BRICK SPEAKS SPANISH]

05:54.752 --> 05:56.251
- Better calm that down.
- BRICK: Calm down.

05:56.253 --> 05:57.820
Ooh, <i>bueno.</i>

05:57.822 --> 05:58.823
Come make
this money, dawg.

06:00.791 --> 06:03.161
Come over here
and kiss my ass.

06:04.062 --> 06:05.794
Come on, man.

06:05.796 --> 06:07.998
[PICK AND BRICK LAUGHING]

06:08.000 --> 06:09.935
- PICK: Watch this.
- BRICK: Get out of here.

06:11.202 --> 06:12.736
When you got money,

06:12.738 --> 06:14.738
people do for you.

06:14.740 --> 06:17.173
When you don't,
you do for them.

06:17.175 --> 06:19.078
So who you
want to be, Reggie, huh?

06:19.810 --> 06:21.246
Who you want to be?

06:22.947 --> 06:24.748
- Look, man, I told my mom...
- PICK: Your mama?

06:24.750 --> 06:26.815
- Yo, you hear this guy?
- Your mom...

06:26.817 --> 06:29.786
[BOTH LAUGHING]

06:29.788 --> 06:32.022
Will always told me that
you was a mama's boy.

06:32.024 --> 06:35.058
And that's probably the only smart
thing that dead fool ever said.

06:35.060 --> 06:37.027
Because your mom
ain't nothing but a...

06:37.029 --> 06:39.262
BRICK: Hit that boy.

06:39.264 --> 06:41.367
You don't talk
about a boy's mama, man.

06:42.000 --> 06:43.336
[GRUNTING]

06:46.704 --> 06:48.373
Gun. Let's go. Go!

06:59.851 --> 07:01.150
[VIVIAN LAUGHS]

07:01.152 --> 07:03.152
So, I blew him off and I told
him that I would let him know.

07:03.154 --> 07:04.953
Because I want you
to come too.

07:04.955 --> 07:06.455
It's a cop thing
and all.

07:06.457 --> 07:09.092
Me? Oh, no. [CHUCKLES]
I don't think so, Viv.

07:09.094 --> 07:10.359
It's not a double date
or anything.

07:10.361 --> 07:11.428
No.

07:11.430 --> 07:13.395
I want to hang around Reg.

07:13.397 --> 07:14.698
Reg is a big boy.

07:14.700 --> 07:17.332
Are you sure he wants to spend
his Friday night with Mama?

07:17.334 --> 07:18.767
- [CHUCKLES]
- I know.

07:18.769 --> 07:20.436
I know, Viv, but...

07:20.438 --> 07:23.039
What is it with you and
this whole cop thing now?

07:23.041 --> 07:25.842
Well, I have dated everyone
at Children and Youth,

07:25.844 --> 07:27.010
- and it's time to give...
- True.

07:27.012 --> 07:29.012
- ...law enforcement a try.
- [LAUGHS]

07:29.014 --> 07:31.080
Starting with Vice.

07:31.082 --> 07:33.048
[CHUCKLES]

07:33.050 --> 07:34.950
Seriously, Joce,
you should come out.

07:34.952 --> 07:37.486
I mean, who is going to tell
me to keep my panties on,

07:37.488 --> 07:38.654
if you are not there?
[LAUGHS]

07:38.656 --> 07:41.323
- You mean, help you find them at closing.
- [LAUGHING]

07:41.325 --> 07:42.424
- Oi...
- Seriously.

07:42.426 --> 07:44.327
You need to get out.

07:44.329 --> 07:47.464
I told Reg we'd go out
to a movie.

07:47.466 --> 07:50.200
He's not going to be watching
movies with mama forever.

07:50.202 --> 07:53.303
And besides, I told you
I see him with the, uh...

07:53.305 --> 07:55.137
The King girl, Mariah.

07:55.139 --> 07:57.039
The girl with
the woman's body.

07:57.041 --> 08:00.876
- Whoo!
- I'm sure Reg doesn't notice.

08:00.878 --> 08:03.113
He's a teenage boy,
honey. He sees it.

08:03.115 --> 08:04.447
And he wants it.

08:04.449 --> 08:05.748
Hell, I want it.

08:05.750 --> 08:08.217
If I had a tight little booty
like that, I wouldn't need to

08:08.219 --> 08:10.152
just throw myself
at the Vice.

08:10.154 --> 08:12.755
[LAUGHING] They... They
would come looking for me.

08:12.757 --> 08:14.791
- [CHUCKLES]
- Viv, it's like I told you,

08:14.793 --> 08:16.258
Reggie's still adrift.

08:16.260 --> 08:18.193
Ever since
his brother died, he's just

08:18.195 --> 08:20.063
going through the motions.

08:20.065 --> 08:21.263
I know, hon.

08:21.265 --> 08:23.799
Just try to take
a step back for a minute,

08:23.801 --> 08:26.368
and take yourself out
of the picture, I mean,

08:26.370 --> 08:28.003
we've seen this
a million times

08:28.005 --> 08:29.938
- at Children and Youth, right?
- Yes.

08:29.940 --> 08:31.340
And what do we
tell the clients?

08:31.342 --> 08:32.542
Vivian...

08:32.544 --> 08:35.077
Well, what do we
tell the clients?

08:35.078 --> 08:37.279
You have to think
of yourself too.

08:37.280 --> 08:40.385
You have to show them
that life goes on.

08:41.318 --> 08:43.052
I know, Viv.

08:43.054 --> 08:45.357
It's just different when it's
your home that's suffering.

08:49.527 --> 08:50.994
Wait, stop.

08:50.996 --> 08:52.861
Go away.

08:52.863 --> 08:54.230
No. Stop.

08:54.232 --> 08:56.499
- Wait.
- Go away, kid. Don't follow me.

08:56.501 --> 08:59.034
- Just leave me alone.
- Look, I just...

08:59.036 --> 09:00.537
I just want
to thank you.

09:00.539 --> 09:03.872
Yeah, well, don't.
Just forget it.

09:03.874 --> 09:05.308
Forget you ever saw me.

09:05.310 --> 09:07.242
What?

09:07.244 --> 09:08.877
You...
You forgot your...

09:08.879 --> 09:11.581
Oh, wait. Wait. Here.
Here. Here. This...

09:11.583 --> 09:12.952
This is yours.

09:13.584 --> 09:17.120
Okay. Pick and Brick,

09:17.122 --> 09:19.058
they might
have killed me.

09:19.825 --> 09:21.227
Uh, thanks.

09:24.094 --> 09:25.461
Take it. Okay.

09:25.463 --> 09:27.031
They might've
killed you too.

09:28.032 --> 09:29.401
Yeah, thanks
for the money.

09:32.603 --> 09:34.507
Uh, why'd
you do it?

09:38.276 --> 09:39.478
Mister?

09:41.012 --> 09:43.478
You know you don't
have to live here, right?

09:43.480 --> 09:45.582
You shouldn't
live like this.

09:45.584 --> 09:47.449
My mom,
she could help you.

09:47.451 --> 09:48.953
Go home to her.

09:50.354 --> 09:53.088
- I just want to talk to you.
- No.

09:53.090 --> 09:54.993
- I... I just want to...
- Go away! Just...

09:55.860 --> 09:56.995
Go take care of her.

10:02.533 --> 10:04.135
Learn to fight, kid.

10:46.411 --> 10:48.111
JOCELYN: Reggie!

10:48.113 --> 10:49.212
[WATER RUNNING]

10:49.214 --> 10:51.349
[STAMMERS] In the bathroom, Ma.

10:53.017 --> 10:54.920
JOCELYN: Dinner's ready
in five minutes.

10:58.022 --> 10:59.391
Okay.

11:00.525 --> 11:02.024
[WATER STOPS]

11:02.026 --> 11:03.561
[WATER SPLASHING]

11:16.074 --> 11:18.176
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

11:27.651 --> 11:29.454
Mariah!

11:31.055 --> 11:34.490
No, no, no! [SCOFFS]
It's good. I'm cool.

11:34.492 --> 11:37.125
No... Nothing happened.

11:37.127 --> 11:39.194
No, he just gave me
the usual rap,

11:39.196 --> 11:42.000
you know, the world
according to Zeke and blah.

11:43.100 --> 11:44.903
Uh. Tonight?

11:49.140 --> 11:51.043
[SIGHS]

11:52.643 --> 11:54.212
I... I don't think so.

11:56.314 --> 11:58.083
Yeah, maybe tomorrow.

11:58.650 --> 12:00.185
All right.
Talk later.

12:01.151 --> 12:02.353
Bye.

12:03.088 --> 12:04.486
Bye.

12:04.488 --> 12:05.958
[LAUGHS]

12:06.291 --> 12:07.559
Bye. Bye.

12:14.065 --> 12:16.001
[INHALES DEEPLY]

12:19.570 --> 12:22.404
- JOCELYN: Reggie, come on, honey.
- I'm coming, Ma.

12:22.406 --> 12:23.675
[GROANS]

12:25.310 --> 12:28.144
Hey! Ooh!

12:28.146 --> 12:29.544
Hey! [SHOOS AWAY]

12:29.546 --> 12:30.950
Patience.

12:33.050 --> 12:34.453
[IMITATING JOCELYN]
Patience.

12:35.719 --> 12:37.220
How was work?

12:37.222 --> 12:38.257
Great.

12:38.623 --> 12:40.255
Long though.

12:40.257 --> 12:43.058
REGGIE: Great, but, long.

12:43.060 --> 12:45.430
JOCELYN: Can you grab me that
pitcher from the top shelf?

12:46.564 --> 12:48.033
I'll make us
some tea.

12:52.302 --> 12:55.138
Reggie,
what happened?

12:55.140 --> 12:57.109
- Huh? What?
- What's wrong?

12:57.441 --> 12:59.074
Oh, uh,

12:59.076 --> 13:01.711
[LAUGHS] nothing, I pulled
a muscle in gym class.

13:01.713 --> 13:03.279
A muscle?

13:03.281 --> 13:05.581
Yeah, it's a muscle, Mom.

13:05.583 --> 13:08.050
Leave the pitcher.
Come here. Let's talk.

13:08.052 --> 13:09.554
I want to hear
all about it.

13:15.660 --> 13:17.559
Let me make sure
I got this right.

13:17.561 --> 13:19.395
You were fighting
with a homeless man.

13:19.397 --> 13:21.097
No. No, no, no.

13:21.099 --> 13:23.298
He was fighting
Pick and Brick.

13:23.300 --> 13:25.068
Zeke and Theo?
Oh, my God.

13:25.070 --> 13:26.736
- <i>Pero</i> what?
- [CALMLY] Mom. Mom.

13:26.738 --> 13:28.404
It's okay.

13:28.406 --> 13:30.405
What part of this
is okay, Reggie?

13:30.407 --> 13:32.107
Okay.
You don't understand.

13:32.109 --> 13:33.275
All right,
they were hassling me.

13:33.277 --> 13:35.748
And this homeless guy...
This homeless guy, he just...

13:37.081 --> 13:38.713
He just lost it, Mom.

13:38.715 --> 13:42.217
Reg, what have I told you?
To stay away.

13:42.219 --> 13:43.285
You promised me.

13:43.287 --> 13:45.288
Mom, they stopped me.

13:45.290 --> 13:46.655
Okay?
And they were hassling me.

13:46.657 --> 13:48.524
And this homeless guy,
Zeke, was hassling him,

13:48.526 --> 13:51.159
and the next thing I know, he was
standing up to Brick and then...

13:51.161 --> 13:52.797
The homeless guy?

13:53.430 --> 13:54.700
Mom, he was...

13:55.733 --> 13:57.265
He was unbelievable.

13:57.267 --> 13:59.468
Man, he was like...

13:59.470 --> 14:01.571
He was like a boxer
or something. I mean...

14:01.573 --> 14:04.140
[GRUNTING] Bam! Bam!

14:04.142 --> 14:06.675
And the big dummy
was on the ground and...

14:06.677 --> 14:09.347
Really? A homeless guy
did all this?

14:10.647 --> 14:11.783
Who is he?

14:14.319 --> 14:15.717
I don't know.

14:15.719 --> 14:17.886
He was just
some guy walking by.

14:17.888 --> 14:19.724
And what happened?

14:22.493 --> 14:24.062
Reggie.

14:26.363 --> 14:27.666
Zeke.

14:28.666 --> 14:30.500
He hit you.

14:30.502 --> 14:33.502
[MUMBLING] He was talking
about Will and you.

14:33.504 --> 14:35.837
- And?
- And I tried to hit him.

14:35.839 --> 14:37.840
What have I told you?

14:37.842 --> 14:39.375
It doesn't matter
what he says,

14:39.377 --> 14:41.443
you don't do anything,
you don't say anything.

14:41.445 --> 14:44.313
- You just walk away.
- They do not let you walk away.

14:44.315 --> 14:45.517
Reggie...

14:47.352 --> 14:48.520
Please.

14:52.190 --> 14:53.624
I can't lose you too.

14:55.259 --> 14:57.526
Sorry, Mom.

14:57.528 --> 14:59.529
When he starts
talking about Will,

14:59.531 --> 15:01.396
I mean, like he had nothing
to do with that...

15:01.398 --> 15:03.234
I just get so mad.

15:04.268 --> 15:06.869
I know.
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

15:06.871 --> 15:09.808
We just can't let that anger
poison our lives.

15:15.246 --> 15:17.712
I guess, we should give
thanks to the stranger too.

15:17.714 --> 15:20.685
[LAUGHS] Mom,
you should have seen him.

15:21.618 --> 15:23.785
Well, he could be
dangerous too.

15:23.787 --> 15:27.490
- [LAUGHS] No doubt.
- I want you to stay away from him.

15:27.492 --> 15:28.957
What do you mean?
He helped me.

15:28.959 --> 15:30.458
This time,
Reggie, but,

15:30.460 --> 15:32.562
so many of those people
are unstable.

15:32.564 --> 15:35.264
And if he's as talented
as you say he is,

15:35.266 --> 15:37.466
- it could be a scary thing.
- Mom, he...

15:37.468 --> 15:40.903
He wasn't crazy
like the rest of them.

15:40.905 --> 15:43.872
Want to know what he said
right before he beat on Brick?

15:43.874 --> 15:46.644
He said, "You don't talk
about a man's mother."

15:48.478 --> 15:49.978
Maybe so.

15:49.980 --> 15:52.314
But, I want you
to be careful.

15:52.316 --> 15:53.982
And I want you to stay as
far away as possible

15:53.984 --> 15:56.218
from Zeke and Theo,
do you understand?

15:56.220 --> 15:57.720
They're going to want
payback, Reggie.

15:57.722 --> 16:00.423
- And they're not going to care who it is...
- Okay, just...

16:00.425 --> 16:01.957
Just don't go
report him to anyone.

16:01.959 --> 16:04.393
Zeke? [SCOFFS] That's
going to make a difference.

16:04.395 --> 16:06.428
The homeless guy, Mom.

16:06.430 --> 16:07.632
The homeless guy.

16:08.366 --> 16:09.768
After what he did,

16:11.368 --> 16:13.171
- he deserves a medal.
- [CHUCKLES]

16:15.573 --> 16:16.875
Keep that on.

16:19.410 --> 16:20.612
Good.

16:21.613 --> 16:22.781
Love you, Mom.

16:23.448 --> 16:24.847
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

16:24.849 --> 16:25.914
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

16:25.916 --> 16:26.918
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

16:37.695 --> 16:40.265
[SIGHS]

17:20.805 --> 17:22.406
[DOGS BARKING]

17:27.711 --> 17:29.844
Hey, uh,
have you seen a guy,

17:29.846 --> 17:32.448
- this tall, uh...
- Oh, kid...

17:32.450 --> 17:33.783
A kid.

17:33.785 --> 17:35.254
Excuse me, sir?

17:40.825 --> 17:44.060
Excuse me, sir, I'm looking
for a guy, uh, this tall,

17:44.062 --> 17:47.963
rough around the face,
he punches, and...

17:47.965 --> 17:50.399
You must mean Lightning.

17:50.401 --> 17:52.001
Lightning.

17:52.003 --> 17:53.101
[MUMBLING]
He's definitely over there.

17:53.103 --> 17:55.004
No, he's there.

17:55.006 --> 17:57.342
I don't want it!
Get away!

18:02.412 --> 18:05.413
Uh, excuse me, sir, um,

18:05.415 --> 18:07.318
Lightning,
have you seen the guy?

18:35.747 --> 18:39.814
Hey, uh, miss, uh, I think
his name is Lightning.

18:39.816 --> 18:43.886
Lightning! He...
He lives over there, kid.

18:43.888 --> 18:45.324
[LAUGHING]

18:47.557 --> 18:48.626
Over there.

18:53.131 --> 18:56.500
[EFFORT GRUNTING]

19:24.661 --> 19:26.131
[FLY BUZZING]

19:26.898 --> 19:28.400
Who's there?

19:29.734 --> 19:30.736
Who's there?

19:31.035 --> 19:32.838
Go away!

19:33.938 --> 19:35.704
Leave me alone.

19:35.706 --> 19:38.040
Kid, is that you?

19:38.042 --> 19:40.045
You need to stay
away from me!

19:41.077 --> 19:43.047
Leave me alone, please.

19:44.649 --> 19:47.419
[SOBBING] Leave me alone.

19:49.853 --> 19:51.590
[SOBBING]

19:57.461 --> 19:59.928
[METAL CLANGING]

19:59.930 --> 20:03.599
How you doing? Oh!
Good morning, pancakes!

20:03.601 --> 20:04.803
For my hero.

20:05.803 --> 20:07.035
What?

20:07.037 --> 20:09.537
I know you were sticking up
for me and Will yesterday.

20:09.539 --> 20:10.773
Oh, Mom.

20:10.775 --> 20:14.112
I just want you to know that I
understand and appreciate it.

20:14.612 --> 20:16.078
Okay?

20:16.080 --> 20:18.480
We just have to be careful,
if we're going to make it.

20:18.482 --> 20:19.817
Right?

20:20.718 --> 20:22.051
Right?

20:22.053 --> 20:24.122
Oh, yeah. Uh, right.
Right.

20:24.654 --> 20:25.656
Make it.

20:26.790 --> 20:28.924
[LAUGHS]
There's your syrup.

20:28.926 --> 20:31.627
I'm going grocery shopping, honey.
Do you want anything?

20:31.629 --> 20:34.530
Uh, no...
No thanks.

20:34.532 --> 20:37.265
Okay. Enjoy.
See you in a bit.

20:37.267 --> 20:38.737
Bye.

21:56.881 --> 21:59.150
Hey, I... I just wanted
to thank you.

22:01.218 --> 22:03.585
- Properly.
- [COUGHING]

22:03.587 --> 22:06.156
My mom, she made, uh,
some pancakes for me.

22:07.991 --> 22:11.095
She said I was a hero, you know,
for sticking up for her and Will.

22:11.996 --> 22:15.096
But, dude,
you're the hero.

22:15.098 --> 22:16.734
You're the one
who deserves this.

22:25.209 --> 22:26.244
[GULPS]

22:27.944 --> 22:29.745
What do you want, kid?

22:29.747 --> 22:30.815
Nothing.

22:31.348 --> 22:33.649
Then, go.

22:33.651 --> 22:35.554
You thanked me,
you gave me my medal,

22:36.621 --> 22:37.822
get going.

22:42.692 --> 22:44.562
[PLANE FLYING OVERHEAD]

22:48.098 --> 22:50.632
Your name's
Lightning, right?

22:50.634 --> 22:52.970
[SCOFFS AND COUGHS]

22:54.904 --> 22:56.106
Right?

22:58.241 --> 23:00.144
[LAUGHING]
The pancakes were good.

23:02.246 --> 23:04.947
Kid I don't live
in your world.

23:04.949 --> 23:07.218
My world's pretty ugly
and I can get ugly.

23:08.184 --> 23:10.020
Now get the hell
out of here.

23:10.654 --> 23:11.655
[SIGHS]

23:16.794 --> 23:17.796
Who are you?

23:21.832 --> 23:22.968
What are you doing here?

23:25.870 --> 23:27.272
You must've been someone.

23:28.271 --> 23:30.438
A boxer? A boxer, right?

23:30.440 --> 23:32.306
I mean,
is that what you did?

23:32.308 --> 23:33.574
I mean, the way you...

23:33.576 --> 23:37.746
You laid into Brick. You were up
and down that big bully like...

23:37.748 --> 23:38.783
Like he was
your punching bag.

23:39.315 --> 23:40.951
[SIGHS]

23:42.385 --> 23:44.953
Big ones are easy.

23:44.955 --> 23:46.891
They think they
just have to show up.

23:48.726 --> 23:49.861
It's...

23:51.394 --> 23:52.796
It's what?

23:54.097 --> 23:57.099
Sneaky, mean ones,

23:57.101 --> 23:59.901
the ones
that'll do anything...

23:59.903 --> 24:01.405
You can see it
in their eyes.

24:02.907 --> 24:04.309
Like...
Like Pick?

24:13.350 --> 24:14.819
What do you want, kid?

24:16.921 --> 24:18.657
Leave me alone.

24:19.422 --> 24:21.355
[PLANE FLYING OVERHEAD]

24:21.357 --> 24:24.392
REGGIE: Wait! Wait!

24:24.394 --> 24:26.762
Yesterday you said something.
You said, "Learn to fight."

24:26.764 --> 24:29.100
How am I going to do that? Who's
going to teach... I don't have anyone!

24:46.083 --> 24:47.719
Yeah, street punks,
you know,

24:48.251 --> 24:49.918
they're all the same.

24:49.920 --> 24:53.188
They just got a few moves
and lots of attitude.

24:53.190 --> 24:55.123
What are you doing? I'm
just trying to thank you.

24:55.125 --> 24:56.227
Huh?
Want to thank me?

24:56.861 --> 24:57.862
Thank this?

24:58.394 --> 24:59.698
[GRUNTS]

25:01.364 --> 25:02.834
Over here.

25:03.500 --> 25:05.002
[GRUNTS]

25:12.843 --> 25:14.877
Watch the footwork.

25:14.879 --> 25:16.214
Yeah,
it's the footwork, huh?

25:17.515 --> 25:19.050
That's right.

25:19.850 --> 25:21.151
Keep your feet
under you.

25:22.219 --> 25:23.921
Now it's your turn.

25:34.864 --> 25:36.166
A guy rushes you.

25:38.235 --> 25:41.039
Kid, you don't
back straight up.

25:42.338 --> 25:44.406
What you got to do is

25:44.408 --> 25:47.275
give him an angle.
Step to the side and pivot.

25:47.277 --> 25:48.445
See?

25:50.014 --> 25:51.913
Step to the side
and roll under.

25:51.915 --> 25:54.448
Then, only then,
you strike.

25:54.450 --> 25:56.019
[GRUNTS]

25:56.821 --> 25:57.988
See?

25:59.155 --> 26:01.189
Wait for it.

26:01.191 --> 26:03.225
Sooner or later,

26:03.227 --> 26:04.996
every big guy
is going to rush you.

26:08.598 --> 26:10.299
And it's your turn.

26:10.301 --> 26:12.170
Then, it's your turn.

26:15.538 --> 26:17.206
- Go?
- Go.

26:17.208 --> 26:19.274
Come on, kid.
[LAUGHS]

26:19.276 --> 26:21.843
Come on, kid.
I'm coming to get you.

26:21.845 --> 26:23.180
I'm coming to get you.

26:24.949 --> 26:26.215
Okay. I'm okay.

26:26.217 --> 26:27.349
Let's go.
Come on, kid.

26:27.351 --> 26:29.353
Yeah, attaboy.
Come on.

26:31.221 --> 26:33.255
[GRUNTS] That's it.

26:33.257 --> 26:35.056
Keep moving.
Keep moving.

26:35.058 --> 26:36.992
Keep moving.

26:36.994 --> 26:40.161
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]
- Come on.

26:40.163 --> 26:41.863
Kid.

26:41.865 --> 26:43.867
[PANTING]

26:45.199 --> 26:45.536
[SIGHS]

26:47.537 --> 26:50.141
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

26:52.543 --> 26:53.945
Not bad.

26:59.350 --> 27:02.821
[GRUNTS]

27:15.098 --> 27:17.100
Why are you
doing this, kid?

27:17.934 --> 27:19.400
I got to...

27:19.402 --> 27:21.271
I got to learn
to protect myself.

27:23.106 --> 27:24.408
Protect my mom.

27:31.015 --> 27:32.917
You know why you didn't
hit that punk yesterday?

27:35.018 --> 27:36.353
Why?

27:37.321 --> 27:38.890
You weren't
ready to hit him.

27:39.422 --> 27:41.555
Yeah, you were mad.

27:41.557 --> 27:43.193
You wanted to hit him.

27:44.260 --> 27:45.896
You weren't ready.

27:49.132 --> 27:52.199
You weren't
in position to strike.

27:52.201 --> 27:53.936
See, that's what
it's all about.

27:53.938 --> 27:56.440
You gotta be in position
to strike first.

27:57.507 --> 27:59.177
Be where you need to be.

28:00.443 --> 28:01.645
What do you mean?

28:05.716 --> 28:09.284
So, who you going to watch
your movies with now, Mama?

28:09.286 --> 28:11.687
[CHUCKLES]

28:11.689 --> 28:14.089
Be grateful,
she's a smart girl,

28:14.091 --> 28:15.990
and she's in school
and she isn't some little

28:15.992 --> 28:18.526
hoochie-coochie
on the street, right?

28:18.528 --> 28:20.562
- Amen to that.
- [LAUGHING]

28:20.564 --> 28:22.264
Oh, is that
where he's at?

28:22.266 --> 28:24.265
Oh, yeah. Soon as
we got home from church.

28:24.267 --> 28:27.201
Off to work on
his project with Mariah.

28:27.203 --> 28:29.438
Aye,
now don't you worry.

28:29.440 --> 28:31.707
- He's always going to be your boy.
- [SIGHS]

28:31.709 --> 28:33.342
Viv.

28:33.344 --> 28:36.111
Have a boy of your own,
then tell me not to worry.

28:36.113 --> 28:37.146
[LAUGHS]

28:37.148 --> 28:40.118
You know, it's not
Mariah or girls, I worry about,

28:40.484 --> 28:41.550
I know.

28:41.552 --> 28:44.619
It's just growing up
here, in this.

28:44.621 --> 28:46.688
You know he had a run in
with Zeke the other day,

28:46.690 --> 28:48.090
after school?

28:48.092 --> 28:49.425
Zeke?

28:49.427 --> 28:53.061
- He's the one with the, uh... [SPEAKING SPANISH]
- Yeah, the ice pick.

28:53.063 --> 28:55.229
Guess he followed Reg home.

28:55.231 --> 28:56.497
He hit him.

28:56.499 --> 28:58.033
What?

28:58.035 --> 29:00.302
- What for?
- You know what he's all about.

29:00.304 --> 29:03.104
Getting kids
to deal for him.

29:03.106 --> 29:05.474
- So, he did what...
- VIVIAN: You don't think Reg would?

29:05.476 --> 29:07.575
My Reg, oh, Lord, no.

29:07.577 --> 29:09.678
He would rather cut off
his hand than do that.

29:09.680 --> 29:11.045
Not after watching
his brother

29:11.047 --> 29:12.280
go down
that road.

29:12.282 --> 29:14.282
Right.
So why he hit him?

29:14.284 --> 29:17.689
Well, Reggie said,
he tried to hit Zeke first.

29:19.789 --> 29:22.225
He said that he was
talking about me and Will.

29:24.694 --> 29:26.697
He can't go doing that.

29:28.498 --> 29:31.332
He can't always
walk away either.

29:31.334 --> 29:34.201
He's gotta learn
to take care of himself.

29:34.203 --> 29:36.606
The Zekes of the world,
they ain't going away.

29:37.373 --> 29:39.107
I know.

29:39.109 --> 29:40.542
And get this. Reggie said,

29:40.544 --> 29:42.276
that they were also
hassling some guy,

29:42.278 --> 29:43.178
some homeless guy,

29:43.180 --> 29:45.112
and that the guy,
the homeless guy...

29:45.114 --> 29:46.281
[SCOFFS]

29:46.283 --> 29:50.217
- ...beat the hell out of Theo, Zeke's big muscle.
- Yeah.

29:50.219 --> 29:52.420
What? [LAUGHS]

29:52.422 --> 29:55.323
- Do you believe that?
- [SCOFFS]

29:55.325 --> 29:57.426
He said the guy
beat him up and down,

29:57.428 --> 30:00.094
threw him on the ground. Hit
Zeke too and then chased him off.

30:00.096 --> 30:02.831
[GASPS] Oh, my
God, this is crazy.

30:02.833 --> 30:05.332
[SPEAKS SPANISH]
You joking, right?

30:05.334 --> 30:06.634
Well, that was my week.

30:06.636 --> 30:08.338
- How was yours?
- Mmm.

30:08.604 --> 30:10.304
Wait.

30:10.306 --> 30:12.140
I didn't ask you
about the cop thing.

30:12.142 --> 30:13.809
- Mmm...
- And?

30:13.811 --> 30:16.511
Eh, it's not bad.
But, I think the boys in blue

30:16.513 --> 30:19.214
were on their
best behavior for me.

30:19.216 --> 30:20.849
So, you had to keep
your panties on.

30:20.851 --> 30:23.284
[BOTH LAUGH]

30:23.286 --> 30:26.854
But, they're good guys, and
they know how to treat a lady.

30:26.856 --> 30:29.157
You know, I think we should
double up next time.

30:29.159 --> 30:32.127
Mmm. Uh... Maybe.

30:32.129 --> 30:34.696
- Sure.
- Hmm? A maybe? A...

30:34.698 --> 30:38.332
[LAUGHS] Big changes
in the whole household.

30:38.334 --> 30:39.834
Big changes. [GASPS]

30:39.836 --> 30:41.469
I'm going to
hold you to that.

30:41.471 --> 30:43.170
Okay, thank you.

30:43.172 --> 30:45.239
- Anything you want.
- I told you, I see it in the future.

30:45.241 --> 30:48.376
[LAUGHING]
This is good.

30:48.378 --> 30:50.782
- Ah, I'm going to have to go to the gym.
- [LAUGHS]

30:59.555 --> 31:01.223
Got to move around.

31:01.225 --> 31:02.593
Relax.

31:05.362 --> 31:07.129
Just punches
and punches.

31:07.131 --> 31:08.599
[GRUNTS]

31:09.533 --> 31:11.168
Uppercuts and hooks.

31:12.199 --> 31:12.434
Bam, bam, bam, bam!

31:12.436 --> 31:14.201
That's it. Uppercuts
and hooks to the body.

31:14.203 --> 31:15.637
Bam! Bam!

31:15.639 --> 31:17.671
[GRUNTING]

31:17.673 --> 31:19.341
Just Keep moving. Yeah.

31:19.343 --> 31:20.812
Ooh. Keep moving.
Keep moving.

31:22.345 --> 31:25.246
Now we're walking.
Now we're walking.

31:25.248 --> 31:27.282
Let me see you jab.
Come on.

31:27.284 --> 31:28.717
Come on, let's go.

31:28.719 --> 31:30.451
Yeah.
Get up.

31:30.453 --> 31:33.354
Move.
Side to side. Relax.

31:33.356 --> 31:34.589
Come on, stay loose.

31:34.591 --> 31:36.257
- Stay loose, shoulders loose.
- All right.

31:36.259 --> 31:37.559
- Kid, move.
- Okay.

31:37.561 --> 31:38.563
Kid, move.

31:40.497 --> 31:42.800
[GRAVEL RUSTLING]

31:44.401 --> 31:45.934
Move around.

31:45.936 --> 31:47.371
Side to side.

31:48.505 --> 31:49.774
Side to side.

31:51.341 --> 31:53.744
Come on.
No, no, no. No.

31:54.878 --> 31:57.278
Side to side.
Left leg leads.

31:57.280 --> 31:59.480
Lead leg.
Now, don't cross your legs.

31:59.482 --> 32:01.451
All right, stand.

32:02.853 --> 32:05.288
Work a jab.
Work your jab.

32:05.855 --> 32:07.822
Work your jab.

32:07.824 --> 32:09.791
That's your rear hand,
that's you right...

32:09.793 --> 32:11.592
- That's your cross, your jab, your lead...
- Yeah, but

32:11.594 --> 32:12.893
- this one feels good.
- No, no.

32:12.895 --> 32:15.229
Because it's
the power hand.

32:15.231 --> 32:16.831
You get...
You got to... [GRUNTS]

32:16.833 --> 32:18.967
It's a right hand,
it's power hand.

32:18.969 --> 32:20.869
So, you wait
after you jab,

32:20.871 --> 32:23.838
you jab and then you throw the right.
You throw the right!

32:23.840 --> 32:25.840
Let me see you
do your jab, kid.

32:25.842 --> 32:28.543
Jab, jab. Jab.

32:28.545 --> 32:30.312
- [GRUNTS]
- Not that.

32:30.314 --> 32:31.746
- That's the...
- I got it.

32:31.748 --> 32:33.814
Stay... Kid.

32:33.816 --> 32:35.185
Listen.

32:36.519 --> 32:37.820
- What?
- It's...

32:37.822 --> 32:40.221
This ain't working. I don't
know if I'm the guy for this.

32:40.223 --> 32:41.625
No, no, no,
I can do it.

32:42.526 --> 32:43.928
- Just...
- Jab. Jab.

32:45.394 --> 32:47.394
No, no, no,
don't cross your feet.

32:47.396 --> 32:49.464
You don't cross your feet,
somebody'll push you,

32:49.466 --> 32:51.699
you'll get knocked down
to the ground.

32:51.701 --> 32:53.467
You don't do it,
it's technique.

32:53.469 --> 32:55.637
It's important.
Technique's important!

32:55.639 --> 32:56.871
- Lightning...
- Like Paddy taught!

32:56.873 --> 32:58.640
It's all right, Lightning.

32:58.642 --> 33:00.242
- Paddy.
- I... I can...

33:00.244 --> 33:01.379
Technique is important!

33:01.711 --> 33:02.879
[SCREAMS]

33:06.415 --> 33:08.385
[GRUNTING]

33:09.920 --> 33:11.453
[MUTTERING]

33:11.455 --> 33:13.324
[GRUNTING]

33:17.026 --> 33:18.493
Right hand! Right hand!

33:18.495 --> 33:19.628
Right hand! Right hand!

33:19.630 --> 33:21.465
Right hand, left!
Right hand, left!

33:24.634 --> 33:26.636
[GRUNTING]

33:32.308 --> 33:34.678
[SCREAMS]

33:43.987 --> 33:46.657
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

33:46.989 --> 33:48.659
Kid!

34:53.755 --> 34:56.326
CORNERMAN: <i>Lightning,
you've got to get up.</i>

35:04.968 --> 35:06.803
[RING BELL DINGING]

35:14.143 --> 35:16.046
So, you excited about
the dance Friday?

35:16.712 --> 35:18.413
Something like that.

35:18.415 --> 35:20.147
I got this
really sexy dress.

35:20.149 --> 35:21.449
It's going to be
a lot of fun.

35:21.451 --> 35:22.549
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

35:22.551 --> 35:23.750
Who you going with?

35:23.752 --> 35:26.587
Oh, well, now since you
asked that, probably Eddie.

35:26.589 --> 35:28.690
- Well, he's not that cute, so...
- Mmm, okay.

35:28.692 --> 35:30.058
And besides,
Stacy asked me out.

35:30.060 --> 35:32.159
- Really?
- Yeah, it was a great proposal.

35:32.161 --> 35:34.828
[CHUCKLES] I mean, no one else
asked me, so...

35:34.830 --> 35:37.699
Oh, come on, that...
That's not fair.

35:37.701 --> 35:39.134
[CHUCKLES]

35:39.136 --> 35:41.569
Ooh, all right,
I got to go.

35:41.571 --> 35:43.804
- What?
- Gotta go.

35:43.806 --> 35:45.172
I thought we were supposed
to go to the library.

35:45.174 --> 35:47.174
REGGIE:
That was your plan.

35:47.176 --> 35:49.411
You were supposed to
help me with it.

35:49.413 --> 35:50.548
Reggie!

35:51.982 --> 35:53.417
Yo, Lightning.

35:55.484 --> 35:56.853
Lightning, yo!

36:00.489 --> 36:01.892
[SCREAMS] Yo, Lightning.

36:08.531 --> 36:09.834
Yo, Lightning.

36:17.473 --> 36:18.808
[PLANE FLYING OVERHEAD]

36:24.047 --> 36:25.683
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

36:27.651 --> 36:29.650
Hey, what the hell
are you doing?

36:29.652 --> 36:31.752
Lightning, yo.

36:31.754 --> 36:33.089
Where'd you get
all this?

36:34.690 --> 36:35.890
What?

36:35.892 --> 36:37.158
You?

36:37.160 --> 36:39.794
Well, you come around there
growling like a bear and stuff.

36:39.796 --> 36:41.931
Yeah, well, come on,
let's patch this stuff up.

36:43.466 --> 36:44.933
Come on.

36:44.935 --> 36:47.100
- Yo, where'd you get all this stuff?
- [SIGHS]

36:47.102 --> 36:49.069
That old gym down
on Philbert Street.

36:49.071 --> 36:50.871
- My old gym.
- [GASPS]

36:50.873 --> 36:53.141
I knew it. So you are
from around here.

36:53.143 --> 36:54.576
Once upon a time.

36:54.578 --> 36:56.643
Well, you got
to take me. Please?

36:56.645 --> 36:58.212
No. It's been
shut down for years.

36:58.214 --> 36:59.883
Nothing but rats and garbage.

37:01.084 --> 37:03.817
Here, I got this for you.

37:03.819 --> 37:05.955
- That's a...
- It's all we got, kid.

37:06.823 --> 37:08.058
Put it on.

37:08.892 --> 37:10.127
Yeah.

37:11.594 --> 37:13.161
Your head.

37:13.163 --> 37:15.599
[STAMMERING]
Yeah, okay.

37:17.933 --> 37:20.768
- Of course, we should wash it first.
- Oh, come on.

37:20.770 --> 37:22.569
[CHUCKLES]
Relax. Hey.

37:22.571 --> 37:24.004
Look what I got you.

37:24.006 --> 37:26.609
You don't have to put those on your head.
Put these on.

37:27.877 --> 37:30.046
Real deal boxing mitts.
Come on, put them on.

37:31.714 --> 37:34.484
- [VELCRO RIPPING]
- Come on, man.

37:37.286 --> 37:39.189
You'll never know
whose hands were in those.

37:42.826 --> 37:44.195
Thanks, man.

37:49.665 --> 37:51.031
Keep your hands up.

37:51.033 --> 37:53.134
- Oh, you don't want this.
- Hands up.

37:53.136 --> 37:54.569
- No way.
- Jab.

37:54.571 --> 37:56.237
Let's see that jab.

37:56.239 --> 37:58.007
[LAUGHING]

38:03.046 --> 38:04.080
[INAUDIBLE]

38:29.772 --> 38:31.241
[INAUDIBLE]

39:04.373 --> 39:07.310
[TRAIN HORN BLOWING]

40:24.353 --> 40:26.756
[BRAKES SCREECHING]

40:28.857 --> 40:30.660
[DOGS BARKING]

40:41.071 --> 40:43.071
Come on, kid.

40:43.073 --> 40:44.772
I'm going to teach you
about trapping.

40:44.774 --> 40:46.109
Trapping?

40:51.413 --> 40:52.982
Just get the kid
out of the way.

40:57.986 --> 40:59.722
Reggie, call it out.

41:00.390 --> 41:02.058
Jab, jab.

41:02.357 --> 41:03.891
Jab.

41:03.893 --> 41:06.194
- Jab!
- [GRUNTS]

41:06.196 --> 41:07.395
Come on, send him up.

41:07.397 --> 41:08.730
[GRUNTS]

41:08.732 --> 41:10.434
[GRUNTING]

41:15.337 --> 41:17.841
Jab, cross. Jab, cross.

41:19.475 --> 41:21.475
- You wanna go?
- REGGIE: Lightning, knife!

41:21.477 --> 41:23.009
No more of
that macho stuff.

41:23.011 --> 41:24.814
- REGGIE: Knife!
- THUG: Your homeless hero's busy.

41:27.750 --> 41:29.484
[GRUNTING]

41:29.486 --> 41:30.752
[GRUNTS]

41:30.754 --> 41:31.922
[GROANS]

41:36.426 --> 41:37.928
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

41:40.330 --> 41:41.799
[GROANS]

41:42.531 --> 41:44.901
[GRUNTING]

42:01.049 --> 42:03.317
Hey,
little school girl.

42:03.319 --> 42:05.353
Where's your boyfriend?

42:05.355 --> 42:10.257
He really shouldn't let a sweet little
treat like you walk home by yourself.

42:10.259 --> 42:11.893
I just want to talk
to you, sweetheart.

42:11.895 --> 42:13.094
- MARIAH: Stop it.
- Hey!

42:13.096 --> 42:15.263
I just want to talk.

42:15.265 --> 42:18.232
- [GRUNTS]
- You know why they call me Pick, baby?

42:18.234 --> 42:19.500
Huh?

42:19.502 --> 42:21.569
I don't give a damn
how sweet you smell,

42:21.571 --> 42:23.804
I will pick your ass apart.

42:23.806 --> 42:25.007
[SOBBING]

42:30.145 --> 42:31.180
Nice piece.

42:32.015 --> 42:33.380
Don't touch it.

42:33.382 --> 42:35.949
- Reggie gave it to...
- Shh.

42:35.951 --> 42:37.919
Yeah, I got
a gift for Reggie.

42:37.921 --> 42:41.254
[DOGS BARKING]

42:41.256 --> 42:44.292
You see to it that Reggie
gets his hands on this.

42:44.294 --> 42:46.797
Okay? He'll know
what to do with it.

42:51.067 --> 42:52.600
Shh.

42:52.602 --> 42:54.270
- [WHIMPERS]
- [CHUCKLES]

43:01.176 --> 43:02.976
[RAPID KNOCKING AT DOOR]

43:02.978 --> 43:04.911
Reggie? Reggie!

43:04.913 --> 43:06.214
- REGGIE: Mom!
- Reggie!

43:06.216 --> 43:08.049
- Come on, come on. Come on.
- No, who is he?

43:08.051 --> 43:09.482
- What's going on?
- Mom, this is Lightning. Come on.

43:09.484 --> 43:10.551
- LIGHTNING: No. No!
- What happened?

43:10.553 --> 43:11.618
Nothing happened.
He's hurt.

43:11.620 --> 43:12.886
Wait, are you hurt, honey?

43:12.888 --> 43:13.922
Mom, stop.
I'm okay, all right?

43:13.924 --> 43:15.422
There was a fight
and he took a knife for me.

43:15.424 --> 43:17.024
- We need to get him in.
- Reggie, I am not a doctor.

43:17.026 --> 43:18.091
Mom, you studied
to be a nurse.

43:18.093 --> 43:20.094
Okay, you study this
kind of thing all the time.

43:20.096 --> 43:21.429
I see you practicing your books.
Now, help me get him in.

43:21.431 --> 43:22.263
- [STAMMERING] Okay, we'll take him to the hospital.
- LIGHTNING: No.

43:22.265 --> 43:23.498
Stay right here.
Just wait right here.

43:23.500 --> 43:26.533
- No, I told you, no doctors, no hospitals.
- Wait, wait, wait.

43:26.535 --> 43:29.402
- Stop, stop. Stop. Mom...
- Reggie, I can't.

43:29.404 --> 43:31.371
Mom, Mom, Mom, this is
the guy that helped me.

43:31.373 --> 43:33.940
- I can't do it.
- Mom, please.

43:33.942 --> 43:35.275
This is the guy
that helped me.

43:35.277 --> 43:38.045
- Remember?
- Reggie, I... [STAMMERS]

43:38.047 --> 43:39.413
Just put him
in the kitchen.

43:39.415 --> 43:41.882
Come on. Lightning,
let me help you.

43:41.884 --> 43:44.252
Okay? You helped me.
Now, let me repay the favor.

43:44.254 --> 43:46.022
- Come on.
- Just...

43:50.926 --> 43:52.328
What's your name?

43:56.466 --> 43:58.165
Lightning.

43:58.167 --> 43:59.634
- Not some street name.
- [SIGHS]

43:59.636 --> 44:00.967
Your real name.

44:00.969 --> 44:03.040
It's not a street name.
It was my...

44:03.473 --> 44:04.474
Nevermind.

44:04.940 --> 44:06.306
[GRUNTS]

44:06.308 --> 44:07.544
Well?

44:08.477 --> 44:10.113
Just call me Lightning.

44:10.580 --> 44:12.179
I will not.

44:12.181 --> 44:14.147
Everyone has
a proper name.

44:14.149 --> 44:15.352
What's yours?

44:18.421 --> 44:19.890
Rodney.

44:21.024 --> 44:22.292
Rhodes.

44:24.326 --> 44:27.060
Rodney, I'm Jocelyn Hall.

44:27.062 --> 44:30.931
Reggie, can you please give me
some towels from the laundry?

44:30.933 --> 44:32.565
And get me
an old shirt of Will's.

44:32.567 --> 44:34.904
- And a T-shirt.
- REGGIE: Okay.

44:39.408 --> 44:41.044
How does that feel?

44:41.544 --> 44:43.046
Wonderful.

44:47.283 --> 44:49.716
You made quite
an impression on Reggie.

44:49.718 --> 44:51.454
Yeah, well,
he's a good kid.

44:53.989 --> 44:55.258
Thank you.

44:58.393 --> 45:00.129
It's not easy.

45:01.096 --> 45:02.265
What's that?

45:04.299 --> 45:06.335
A mother,
to raise a good son.

45:08.337 --> 45:11.040
No, sir. It's not.

45:12.442 --> 45:14.144
I wish you would see a doctor.

45:14.609 --> 45:15.611
So, who's Will?

45:20.716 --> 45:21.919
Reggie's brother.

45:22.685 --> 45:23.750
So, he's the reason

45:23.752 --> 45:25.453
for the bad blood
with the punks, huh?

45:25.455 --> 45:28.556
That Zeke, sucked him in.

45:28.558 --> 45:30.623
Got him into dealing.

45:30.625 --> 45:33.029
It wasn't long until
Will started using.

45:34.529 --> 45:36.198
After that,

45:38.234 --> 45:40.469
you know the story,
you've been around.

45:42.471 --> 45:43.640
I'm sorry.

45:45.674 --> 45:47.410
Reggie was devastated.

45:48.343 --> 45:49.712
Just about killed him.

45:52.247 --> 45:54.483
He still hasn't
come to terms with it.

45:56.585 --> 45:58.622
- But...
- But what?

46:01.390 --> 46:03.093
Meeting you has helped.

46:03.526 --> 46:04.995
[MUMBLING]

46:06.462 --> 46:08.065
Thanks.

46:10.500 --> 46:12.466
Well, I don't want
to insult you,

46:12.468 --> 46:14.768
but, you stink,
you're dirty,

46:14.770 --> 46:17.173
so take off your clothes
and jump in the shower.

46:18.306 --> 46:19.509
Come on.

46:20.676 --> 46:22.011
Yeah.

46:22.411 --> 46:24.145
Got it.

46:24.147 --> 46:25.681
[GROANS SOFTLY]

46:29.518 --> 46:31.354
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

46:32.587 --> 46:34.457
[CHUCKLES] Yeah, I'm home.

46:39.796 --> 46:42.263
JOCELYN: Reg,
where are those towels?

46:42.265 --> 46:44.167
Uh, I'm coming, Mom.

46:52.542 --> 46:54.011
[KNOCKING]

46:56.078 --> 46:57.381
It's just me.

46:58.281 --> 46:59.716
I brought some towels.

47:02.551 --> 47:04.020
I'm setting them here.

47:04.687 --> 47:06.189
Thank you.

47:11.160 --> 47:14.163
Rodney,
what are we going to do?

47:14.696 --> 47:16.797
We?

47:16.799 --> 47:19.433
You just met me,
you don't even know me.

47:19.435 --> 47:22.536
Yes, but,
you're involved now.

47:22.538 --> 47:24.672
Not just
because of today, but,

47:24.674 --> 47:27.808
you've become
part of Reggie's life.

47:27.810 --> 47:30.243
That's what happens when you
make an impression on someone.

47:30.245 --> 47:31.414
No.

47:31.848 --> 47:33.714
No?

47:33.716 --> 47:35.815
You don't want that.

47:35.817 --> 47:37.486
You don't want me involved.

47:39.455 --> 47:41.221
Mr. Rhodes.

47:41.223 --> 47:44.525
We're all in this together,
Whether you like it or not.

47:44.527 --> 47:45.859
No.

47:45.861 --> 47:48.529
Sorry, there no "we."

47:48.531 --> 47:50.563
Nothing good
can come of that.

47:50.565 --> 47:52.866
It never does,
when I'm involved. Just...

47:52.868 --> 47:55.271
Just let me go
and I'll walk away.

47:56.605 --> 47:58.607
- Everyone will be better off that way.
- [SHOWER TURNS OFF]

48:08.384 --> 48:10.087
I'm sorry.

48:21.830 --> 48:24.334
[SOBBING]

48:29.805 --> 48:31.440
[DOG BARKING]

48:32.274 --> 48:34.243
[SOBBING]

48:36.578 --> 48:38.281
- [MARIAH WHIMPERS]
- Come on in, Mariah.

48:39.681 --> 48:41.614
What's... What's wrong?

48:41.616 --> 48:43.917
What happened?
You okay?

48:43.919 --> 48:45.518
When I was heading home,

48:45.520 --> 48:48.489
[SOBBING] Pick,

48:48.491 --> 48:50.623
he stopped me.

48:50.625 --> 48:52.261
That's where he was.

48:52.661 --> 48:54.460
What?

48:54.462 --> 48:56.730
No. There was
a fight with Brick...

48:56.732 --> 48:58.632
Oh, I'm sorry, did he hurt you?

48:58.634 --> 49:00.201
Are... Are you okay?

49:00.203 --> 49:03.837
- No. I'm... I mean, I'm okay.
- You... You sure?

49:03.839 --> 49:05.772
He didn't do anything.

49:05.774 --> 49:06.809
[SOBBING]

49:08.944 --> 49:11.381
But, what happened?

49:12.348 --> 49:14.451
He gave me this.

49:16.986 --> 49:18.986
What?

49:18.988 --> 49:21.855
He wanted to make sure
I gave them to you.

49:21.857 --> 49:24.227
You're supposed
to sell them.

49:25.627 --> 49:28.328
Reg, this is what you've
been doing, isn't it?

49:28.330 --> 49:31.265
No. No! No, okay?
I hate that stuff.

49:31.267 --> 49:32.565
All right, that's not me.

49:32.567 --> 49:33.770
Hey, you know me.

49:35.270 --> 49:36.439
Okay?

49:37.607 --> 49:38.973
[SOBBING]
Reggie, I'm scared.

49:38.975 --> 49:40.177
I'm so sorry.

49:42.978 --> 49:44.247
What are we
going to do?

49:44.714 --> 49:45.846
I don't know.

49:45.848 --> 49:47.880
Reggie,
what's going on?

49:47.882 --> 49:49.819
Mariah, what happened?

49:50.285 --> 49:51.287
Sweetie.

49:52.455 --> 49:54.591
[DOG BARKING]

50:02.464 --> 50:03.864
But why Mariah?

50:03.866 --> 50:06.567
He could've just stopped
me like he's done before.

50:06.569 --> 50:08.301
You would've
just said no.

50:08.303 --> 50:09.338
This way,
you're stuck with it.

50:09.805 --> 50:10.806
I guess.

50:11.774 --> 50:13.440
I'm sorry, Reggie.

50:13.442 --> 50:14.243
RODNEY: He's telling
you something.

50:16.911 --> 50:19.515
Heh. He gets to
the people you love.

50:20.382 --> 50:22.850
That's how
cowards operate.

50:22.852 --> 50:24.853
[STAMMERING] I'm not gonna
let anything happen to you.

50:25.488 --> 50:26.819
Okay?

50:26.821 --> 50:28.321
This is between
Zeke and me.

50:28.323 --> 50:29.455
Just what to do
you think you're gonna do?

50:29.457 --> 50:31.357
REGGIE:
I don't know, all right?

50:31.359 --> 50:33.761
But I'm gonna tell him
he do this, all right?

50:33.763 --> 50:35.029
He doesn't threaten her,

50:35.031 --> 50:36.864
or you, or anyone
that I care about.

50:36.866 --> 50:39.667
All right,
this is between us.

50:39.669 --> 50:42.603
No, you don't go near him.
You'll be playing his game.

50:42.605 --> 50:45.406
Don't... Reggie, your mom, she's...
She's right,

50:45.408 --> 50:46.743
I mean, do you think
he's gonna listen to you?

50:47.810 --> 50:50.844
Hey, he's trying
to draw you in.

50:50.846 --> 50:52.916
To engage you
on his terms.

50:53.748 --> 50:55.482
What have I taught you?

50:55.484 --> 50:56.783
[YELLS] What have I taught you?

50:56.785 --> 50:58.585
To strike
when you're ready.

50:58.587 --> 51:00.556
Not when the other guy
wants you to.

51:01.089 --> 51:02.524
That's right.

51:03.692 --> 51:06.263
Well, what are we
supposed to do?

51:07.096 --> 51:08.429
Go to the police.

51:08.431 --> 51:09.562
The cops?

51:09.564 --> 51:10.730
No.

51:10.732 --> 51:12.833
What, are we supposed to
find one, give him the stuff,

51:12.835 --> 51:14.435
and tell him our story?
Come on, Mom.

51:14.437 --> 51:16.904
Reggie, this isn't some
schoolyard scuffle, honey.

51:16.906 --> 51:18.172
Reggie's right,
it won't work.

51:18.174 --> 51:21.507
I mean, it's not gonna even
get the drugs off the street.

51:21.509 --> 51:23.911
You hand them drugs
to the wrong cop,

51:23.913 --> 51:25.645
he'll hand them
right back to Zeke.

51:25.647 --> 51:27.980
Yeah, we go to the cops
and he'll kill us.

51:27.982 --> 51:29.352
You gotta fight.

51:30.453 --> 51:31.884
You gotta beat him
at his own game.

51:31.886 --> 51:34.054
No. No, no. There's not
gonna be any fighting.

51:34.056 --> 51:37.056
[STAMMERS] Reggie, I'm not saying we
go running into a police station. Okay?

51:37.058 --> 51:40.527
But we can't do this alone.
It's just not gonna work. Okay?

51:40.529 --> 51:42.763
Viv, she knows
some cops, some detectives...

51:42.765 --> 51:44.397
Aunt Vivian?

51:44.399 --> 51:46.533
We can talk to them,
off the record.

51:46.535 --> 51:48.067
Okay. We can talk to them
and tell them what's going on

51:48.069 --> 51:50.971
and they can protect us,
okay? They can warn him.

51:50.973 --> 51:54.007
I don't know.
It's something, right?

51:54.009 --> 51:58.679
Let me just talk to them.
Okay, let me just... Please.

51:58.681 --> 52:02.686
Mariah, do you know by when Reggie
had to do this? Did he say anything?

52:02.984 --> 52:04.053
No.

52:05.553 --> 52:07.056
Okay, this is what
we're gonna do.

52:07.656 --> 52:09.025
Okay?

52:10.759 --> 52:13.363
JOCELYN: Now you need to
go home. It's getting late.

52:14.562 --> 52:17.666
Uh, I'll walk
you home. Okay?

52:21.504 --> 52:22.505
[KISSES]

52:34.683 --> 52:36.453
They deserve
better than this.

52:38.154 --> 52:40.120
We all do.

52:40.122 --> 52:42.558
Yeah. I better go, too.

52:43.526 --> 52:44.828
You don't have to
leave, you know.

52:46.462 --> 52:47.864
You can stay
on the couch.

52:48.631 --> 52:50.563
I can't.

52:50.565 --> 52:51.834
What if they
come back for you?

52:52.968 --> 52:56.737
You don't understand,
I can't stay here.

52:56.739 --> 52:59.640
There'll always be
a place for you here.

52:59.642 --> 53:01.777
- If you ever need it.
- Yeah, well,

53:02.977 --> 53:04.446
thanks,

53:05.948 --> 53:06.848
for everything.

53:08.917 --> 53:10.553
Be sure to come back
so I can check on the cut.

53:12.488 --> 53:13.656
Just a scratch.

53:27.669 --> 53:28.704
Good night.

53:29.872 --> 53:30.973
Good night.

54:19.955 --> 54:20.989
[MOUSE CLICKS]

54:28.931 --> 54:30.066
[MOUSE CLICKS]

54:37.906 --> 54:39.209
[MOUSE CLICKS]

54:47.082 --> 54:49.583
NEWSCASTER ON LAPTOP: <i>WGCG
Sports has an exclusive interview</i>

54:49.585 --> 54:52.618
<i>with legendary boxing trainer
and coach, Paddy Grier.</i>

54:52.620 --> 54:55.556
<i>Grier is trainer to boxer
Rodney ' "Lightning Rod" Rhodes,</i>

54:55.558 --> 54:57.324
<i>who went missing, following
the murder of his mother.</i>

54:57.326 --> 54:59.692
<i>And is considered a person
of interest in that case.</i>

54:59.694 --> 55:02.728
<i>Rhodes forfeited Thursday
night's World Title match</i>

55:02.730 --> 55:05.132
<i>when he failed to appear at
preliminary weigh-ins earlier today.</i>

55:05.134 --> 55:08.335
<i>I asked Grier about this
strange chain of events.</i>

55:08.337 --> 55:12.739
<i>Tragic.
This is just tragic.</i>

55:12.741 --> 55:15.945
<i>Mrs. Rhodes, a wonderful
woman, dead like that.</i>

55:17.145 --> 55:19.279
<i>And Lightning missing.</i>

55:19.281 --> 55:21.882
<i>A talented young man like him,</i>

55:21.884 --> 55:25.851
<i>his career just, shattered.</i>

55:25.853 --> 55:30.259
<i>It's sad. Rodney is the most
dedicated fighter I have ever known.</i>

55:31.660 --> 55:33.796
<i>For him to forfeit
this fight,</i>

55:34.296 --> 55:35.995
<i>something's wrong.</i>

55:35.997 --> 55:37.096
- [KNOCKING AT DOOR]
- REGGIE: Mom?

55:37.098 --> 55:38.100
Reggie?

55:42.937 --> 55:44.106
Everything okay?

55:45.674 --> 55:47.607
Yeah.

55:47.609 --> 55:50.613
I mean, Mariah's shaken up
is all, but...

55:51.647 --> 55:53.614
She's fine.

55:53.616 --> 55:54.517
Was she scared?

55:57.185 --> 55:58.888
Is that what you've been
doing with your time?

55:59.721 --> 56:00.823
Training with Rodney?

56:01.390 --> 56:03.656
You mean Lightning?

56:03.658 --> 56:05.193
Yeah, he's been
teaching me to box.

56:06.127 --> 56:07.330
You mean fight?

56:08.696 --> 56:10.330
Reggie, do you think
it's a good idea

56:10.332 --> 56:12.299
to be spending all that time
with a homeless boxer?

56:12.301 --> 56:14.935
Oh, come on, Mom. You talked
to him. He's all right.

56:14.937 --> 56:16.873
Yes, I did, but...

56:17.839 --> 56:18.938
People like Rodney,

56:18.940 --> 56:21.040
you don't really know
who they are.

56:21.042 --> 56:23.377
Okay, I know what
you mean, Mom,

56:23.379 --> 56:25.344
but Lightning's not
like that.

56:25.346 --> 56:27.346
I mean, you can tell right?
And he likes me.

56:27.348 --> 56:29.885
Yes, he does.

56:30.752 --> 56:32.719
He likes you.

56:32.721 --> 56:35.154
Well, I'm off
to bed, Mom.

56:35.156 --> 56:37.024
[KISSES]
Good night.

56:37.026 --> 56:39.225
Good night.
[SIGHS]

56:39.227 --> 56:40.863
[DOOR CLOSES]

56:46.435 --> 56:48.902
<i>Later in the day,
Paddy refuted any speculation</i>

56:48.904 --> 56:51.871
<i>that Lightning may actually be
a suspect in his mother's death.</i>

56:51.873 --> 56:55.308
<i>No, absolutely not.</i>

56:55.310 --> 56:57.747
<i>Rodney was devoted
to that woman.</i>

56:58.913 --> 57:00.681
<i>She raised him by herself</i>

57:00.683 --> 57:02.982
<i>in some pretty rough
circumstances.</i>

57:02.984 --> 57:05.951
<i>She did a fine job.</i>
[EXHALES]

57:05.953 --> 57:08.754
<i>She raised a damn good man.</i>

57:08.756 --> 57:11.693
<i>There's no easy way
for a woman to do that.</i>

57:12.428 --> 57:16.429
[SIGHS] <i>Rodney and I,</i>

57:16.431 --> 57:18.834
<i>we talked a lot about that.</i>

57:49.230 --> 57:51.401
[FIRE CRACKLING INTENSIFIES]

58:14.957 --> 58:17.790
[TRAIN HORN BLARING]

58:17.792 --> 58:20.128
[CROSSING BELL DINGING]

58:49.190 --> 58:52.324
RODNEY: Hey, you did really good today.
I'm proud of you.

58:52.326 --> 58:54.226
[CHUCKLES]
Yeah, yeah.

58:54.228 --> 58:56.429
Hey, how do you
knock out a big guy?

58:56.431 --> 58:59.933
- So, you wanna knock out a big guy?
- Duh!

58:59.935 --> 59:03.904
What you've got to do, is you
gotta throw the overhand right.

59:03.906 --> 59:07.406
Now, it's not easy.
It's not a straight right.

59:07.408 --> 59:11.545
It's a looping punch you gotta
kinda throw it... [GRUNTS]

59:11.547 --> 59:14.313
Now I know
how Paddy felt...

59:14.315 --> 59:16.248
- Paddy?
- ...not being able to do it.

59:16.250 --> 59:17.951
Who's Paddy?

59:17.953 --> 59:19.920
My trainer
from a long time ago.

59:19.922 --> 59:22.087
He got too old,
couldn't fight anymore,

59:22.089 --> 59:23.489
but, you know,
that son of a gun,

59:23.491 --> 59:27.027
he could look into
the soul of a fighter,

59:27.029 --> 59:29.132
find the lion in him
and just unleash it.

59:30.464 --> 59:32.165
He's the one that made
me the fighter I was.

59:32.167 --> 59:33.567
[SCOFFS]
Was?

59:33.569 --> 59:35.271
You mean, the fighter you are.

59:36.337 --> 59:38.940
Yeah, right.
[CHUCKLES]

59:41.210 --> 59:43.844
So, uh, when's your mom
gonna see, uh, the cops?

59:43.846 --> 59:45.178
When's she gonna
talk to them?

59:45.180 --> 59:48.013
Tonight.
Off record.

59:48.015 --> 59:49.982
Off the record,
how?

59:49.984 --> 59:52.953
Sort of a double-date thing
with her friend Vivian.

59:52.955 --> 59:55.422
Reggie, don't
expect anything.

59:55.424 --> 59:57.991
There's nothing
in it for them.

59:57.993 --> 59:59.558
I know, but my mom,
she's, you know,

59:59.560 --> 01:00:01.527
got a lot of faith
in the system.

01:00:01.529 --> 01:00:03.031
Yeah.

01:00:04.498 --> 01:00:06.866
She told me about Will.

01:00:06.868 --> 01:00:08.236
How Zeke
sucked him in.

01:00:09.872 --> 01:00:12.105
Got him dealing.

01:00:12.107 --> 01:00:15.040
And Will started using.

01:00:15.042 --> 01:00:18.377
And after that,
that was it.

01:00:18.379 --> 01:00:20.047
It was all over.

01:00:23.919 --> 01:00:25.087
Reg...

01:00:26.654 --> 01:00:28.089
Reggie,

01:00:29.056 --> 01:00:30.058
that feeling,

01:00:31.125 --> 01:00:32.227
hold on to it.

01:00:49.176 --> 01:00:50.245
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

01:00:53.181 --> 01:00:57.350
[LAUGHTER]

01:00:57.352 --> 01:01:00.420
- That was good.
- Well, good night, I had a good time.

01:01:00.422 --> 01:01:02.522
- Viv, bye.
- [VIVIAN LAUGHING]

01:01:02.524 --> 01:01:05.058
- Wait, let me walk you to the door.
- No, it's okay. Thank you.

01:01:05.060 --> 01:01:07.096
[CHUCKLING]
Whoa.

01:01:08.629 --> 01:01:11.263
I have been waiting
to get you alone.

01:01:11.265 --> 01:01:12.598
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

01:01:12.600 --> 01:01:14.466
Mmm-hmm.

01:01:14.468 --> 01:01:18.006
Listen, uh, I wanna talk
to you about your problem.

01:01:19.308 --> 01:01:21.978
Can, uh,
we go inside?

01:01:24.145 --> 01:01:25.314
Sure.

01:01:35.656 --> 01:01:36.658
Nice house.

01:01:39.627 --> 01:01:42.364
Look, uh, I know
what your problem is.

01:01:43.732 --> 01:01:46.165
And I feel for you.
I really do.

01:01:46.167 --> 01:01:47.269
I think I could help.

01:01:48.404 --> 01:01:50.971
You said without evidence
there was nothing you can do.

01:01:50.973 --> 01:01:53.138
[CHUCKLES]
Martel said that.

01:01:53.140 --> 01:01:54.509
Me, I get it.

01:01:55.576 --> 01:01:56.912
I know about
your son and all.

01:01:58.613 --> 01:02:00.015
I know
your whole story.

01:02:02.216 --> 01:02:05.053
You just want
a little payback.

01:02:06.120 --> 01:02:07.219
I never said that.

01:02:07.221 --> 01:02:09.489
No, no,
of course not.

01:02:09.491 --> 01:02:12.295
But, look, uh, if you
want to play some ball,

01:02:13.361 --> 01:02:15.295
maybe we could help.

01:02:15.297 --> 01:02:17.196
I don't play ball.

01:02:17.198 --> 01:02:19.132
A little
quid pro quo.

01:02:19.134 --> 01:02:20.569
Isn't that what
the lawyers say?

01:02:21.303 --> 01:02:22.701
You do for me,

01:02:22.703 --> 01:02:24.571
- I'll do for you.
- [SCREAMS] No, no!

01:02:24.573 --> 01:02:27.373
Get your hands off.
Get your... [SCREAMS]

01:02:27.375 --> 01:02:29.408
Get your hands
off me!

01:02:29.410 --> 01:02:31.210
Get off!
Get off me!

01:02:31.212 --> 01:02:33.179
- Hmm?
- Get off me!

01:02:33.181 --> 01:02:34.614
I'm no whore!

01:02:34.616 --> 01:02:36.616
No, you're
not a whore.

01:02:36.618 --> 01:02:38.254
Whores are
smarter than you.

01:02:39.654 --> 01:02:42.291
- Here comes your quiet boy now.
- Mom, what's going on?

01:02:43.792 --> 01:02:45.694
Your mother's trying
to save your punk ass.

01:02:47.062 --> 01:02:48.261
But she's too stupid to...

01:02:48.263 --> 01:02:51.096
- Shut up and get outta here.
- JOCELYN: Reggie! No, no.

01:02:51.098 --> 01:02:52.133
[JOCELYN EXCLAIMS]

01:02:53.035 --> 01:02:54.634
- Oh!
- Wait.

01:02:54.636 --> 01:02:55.738
[GRUNTING]

01:02:58.306 --> 01:02:59.371
Oh, yeah?

01:02:59.373 --> 01:03:01.109
[GRUNTING]

01:03:06.614 --> 01:03:08.281
What... What happened?

01:03:08.283 --> 01:03:10.716
- Settle down, Chuck.
- [GRUNTS] What the hell happened?

01:03:10.718 --> 01:03:12.484
You dropped
your left, fat man.

01:03:12.486 --> 01:03:13.719
CHUCK: [GROANS]
Your kid hit me?

01:03:13.721 --> 01:03:15.087
- You're screwed, kid.
- Come on.

01:03:15.089 --> 01:03:17.089
Just like your brother and every
other piece of garbage in this town.

01:03:17.091 --> 01:03:18.290
[JOCELYN SPEAKS SPANISH]

01:03:18.292 --> 01:03:20.128
You're doomed.
You're finished.

01:03:20.495 --> 01:03:22.295
[GROANS]

01:03:22.297 --> 01:03:25.665
If the gangbangers
don't get you, I will!

01:03:25.667 --> 01:03:27.433
- VIVIAN: Are you okay?
- [SNIFFLES]

01:03:27.435 --> 01:03:30.372
- REGGIE: Mom?
- [SOBS]

01:03:31.306 --> 01:03:32.571
[GROANS]

01:03:32.573 --> 01:03:34.339
No, not these people.

01:03:34.341 --> 01:03:35.643
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

01:03:36.578 --> 01:03:38.280
[GROANING]

01:03:41.149 --> 01:03:42.681
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

01:03:42.683 --> 01:03:45.053
Wait right here.
I'll be right back.

01:03:46.587 --> 01:03:48.256
That scumbag
hurt you?

01:03:49.723 --> 01:03:52.192
No, baby,
I'm okay.

01:03:52.194 --> 01:03:53.759
Joce, I am so sorry,

01:03:53.761 --> 01:03:56.562
I had no idea he was
such a... [SIGHS]

01:03:56.564 --> 01:03:58.364
You didn't know.
Don't worry about it.

01:03:58.366 --> 01:04:00.333
I know, but still I...

01:04:00.335 --> 01:04:03.335
[CRYING]

01:04:03.337 --> 01:04:06.138
How about this guy,
huh? [SOBS AND LAUGHS]

01:04:06.140 --> 01:04:07.809
Like he has
got some skills.

01:04:09.877 --> 01:04:11.413
Mr. Rhodes was right.

01:04:12.513 --> 01:04:13.815
You do have talent.

01:04:15.183 --> 01:04:17.250
JOCELYN: You can take
care of yourself.

01:04:17.252 --> 01:04:18.717
I could take care
of you.

01:04:18.719 --> 01:04:20.221
[JOCELYN SNIFFLES]

01:04:23.757 --> 01:04:26.062
[BELLS CHIMING]

01:04:27.863 --> 01:04:29.728
You okay?

01:04:29.730 --> 01:04:31.397
[SCOFFS]
He never touched me.

01:04:31.399 --> 01:04:35.134
[CHUCKLES] Yeah.
I can see that.

01:04:35.136 --> 01:04:37.636
Is he gonna have any trouble
because of this?

01:04:37.638 --> 01:04:39.371
Nah, I don't even think
Chuck'll remember

01:04:39.373 --> 01:04:41.509
but if he does,
I'll take care of it.

01:04:42.310 --> 01:04:43.775
Thank you.

01:04:43.777 --> 01:04:46.478
Oh, I think it's the least
that I can do, right?

01:04:46.480 --> 01:04:47.482
[SCOFFS]

01:04:48.917 --> 01:04:51.551
Where did you learn
to fight like that?

01:04:51.553 --> 01:04:55.621
A friend sort of teaches me
what he knows. It's nothing big.

01:04:55.623 --> 01:04:57.824
Well, he's either
a great teacher,

01:04:57.826 --> 01:04:59.025
or, man, you're a natural,

01:04:59.027 --> 01:05:01.530
'cause I think you should start
competing, get a real coach.

01:05:02.364 --> 01:05:03.496
Really?

01:05:03.498 --> 01:05:05.397
Well, yeah, you're already
better than half of those guys

01:05:05.399 --> 01:05:06.699
at the Police Athletic League.

01:05:06.701 --> 01:05:07.766
[CHUCKLES]

01:05:07.768 --> 01:05:10.203
Well, we have other things
to think about first.

01:05:10.205 --> 01:05:11.904
That's right.

01:05:11.906 --> 01:05:14.410
Yeah, it's a tough one.
Without any evidence...

01:05:16.444 --> 01:05:18.243
You said you destroyed
the drugs, right?

01:05:18.245 --> 01:05:19.478
I did.

01:05:19.480 --> 01:05:21.547
Well, without that,
what do we have?

01:05:21.549 --> 01:05:23.583
Just someone with a grudge

01:05:23.585 --> 01:05:26.219
trying to pitch
a pretty unlikely story.

01:05:26.221 --> 01:05:27.453
No offense.

01:05:27.455 --> 01:05:28.922
We know.

01:05:28.924 --> 01:05:30.526
All right, well,

01:05:31.792 --> 01:05:33.225
let me sleep on it,
and I'll

01:05:33.227 --> 01:05:34.363
see what
I can come up with.

01:05:34.962 --> 01:05:36.529
Thank you.

01:05:36.531 --> 01:05:39.399
Okay. Ready?

01:05:39.401 --> 01:05:40.803
- Yeah.
- Let's go.

01:05:42.337 --> 01:05:44.636
- <i>Ciao, mijo.</i>
- Bye.

01:05:44.638 --> 01:05:46.808
Bye.
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

01:05:47.975 --> 01:05:49.178
Thank you.

01:05:50.344 --> 01:05:51.647
[VIVIAN EXHALES]

01:06:05.826 --> 01:06:08.428
Anyway, he seems
pretty cool.

01:06:08.430 --> 01:06:10.330
And he said he's gonna
see what he can do.

01:06:10.332 --> 01:06:11.964
You're just saying that
cause he liked your boxing.

01:06:11.966 --> 01:06:14.400
[SCOFFS] No.

01:06:14.402 --> 01:06:17.536
Okay, I mean, yeah,
but, no, he was cool.

01:06:17.538 --> 01:06:18.737
I mean, not like
the other guy.

01:06:18.739 --> 01:06:20.942
The other guy was like a
bad cop out of a bad movie.

01:06:21.810 --> 01:06:24.180
Martel, he was cool.

01:06:25.379 --> 01:06:28.647
Besides, Aunt Vivian
likes him, too, so...

01:06:28.649 --> 01:06:31.516
All right, then, I'll talk to
my mom later, call you then?

01:06:31.518 --> 01:06:32.721
Reg, wait.

01:06:34.723 --> 01:06:36.688
I wanna be with you.

01:06:36.690 --> 01:06:40.259
Please. I really wanna
see what you do with him.

01:06:40.261 --> 01:06:41.728
Yeah, but it's kinda
one of those...

01:06:41.730 --> 01:06:44.297
Reg, if it's important to you
then it's important to me.

01:06:44.299 --> 01:06:46.569
- Yeah, but...
- Mmm, please?

01:06:48.602 --> 01:06:50.902
- Come on, Reg.
- Ugh, okay, okay.

01:06:50.904 --> 01:06:52.705
Okay, okay.

01:06:52.707 --> 01:06:54.973
- But, one condition.
- What?

01:06:54.975 --> 01:06:57.277
If Lightning isn't cool
with it, you'll leave.

01:06:57.279 --> 01:06:58.344
- Okay.
- Okay?

01:06:58.346 --> 01:07:00.248
All right, come on.

01:07:19.500 --> 01:07:21.836
She just wanted to see what it
is we do, if it's okay with you.

01:07:25.306 --> 01:07:27.408
She's curious,
you know?

01:07:29.710 --> 01:07:31.310
It's okay with you?

01:07:31.312 --> 01:07:34.379
Uh, yeah. Yeah.

01:07:34.381 --> 01:07:35.783
[LAUGHS]
I mean, yeah.

01:07:38.752 --> 01:07:40.719
Just don't let her
be a distraction.

01:07:40.721 --> 01:07:42.957
[SCOFFS]
What? Huh.

01:07:46.593 --> 01:07:48.863
[BOTH EXHALING RHYTHMICALLY]

01:07:54.602 --> 01:07:57.103
Slip to the left, slip to the right.
[GRUNTING]

01:07:57.105 --> 01:07:58.737
Pow, pow, pow.

01:07:58.739 --> 01:08:02.645
[GRUNTING]

01:08:24.398 --> 01:08:26.401
[SQUEAKING]

01:08:32.773 --> 01:08:34.809
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

01:08:47.154 --> 01:08:49.621
[CAR APPROACHING]

01:08:49.622 --> 01:08:52.024
Come on, let's get out of here.
Time to go.

01:08:52.026 --> 01:08:54.830
[HIP-HOP MUSIC BLARING
FROM CAR RADIO]

01:09:13.046 --> 01:09:14.683
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:09:15.783 --> 01:09:17.486
We should be
good for now.

01:09:24.091 --> 01:09:25.728
[REGGIE GRUNTS]

01:09:27.495 --> 01:09:29.462
- [MAN LAUGHING]
- Shh.

01:09:29.464 --> 01:09:31.966
- [HIP-HOP MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [MAN CONTINUES LAUGHING]

01:09:33.934 --> 01:09:35.935
Mariah, we need to
cut through the court.

01:09:35.937 --> 01:09:37.803
- No, it's scary in there.
- Mariah!

01:09:37.805 --> 01:09:40.807
It's our safest bet,
all right?

01:09:40.809 --> 01:09:42.607
And it's about to rain, come on.

01:09:42.609 --> 01:09:43.911
[THUNDERCLAP]

01:09:46.880 --> 01:09:48.212
[MARIAH PANTING]

01:09:48.215 --> 01:09:49.852
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
wait, wait.

01:09:51.819 --> 01:09:54.152
- [THUNDERCLAP]
- Yo, yo, yo! Hold on.

01:09:54.154 --> 01:09:56.923
Where are you guys
going so fast, huh?

01:09:56.925 --> 01:10:01.093
Theo, look, man, I don't have
any fight with you, all right?

01:10:01.095 --> 01:10:03.795
- We're just trying to get home.
- Get home?

01:10:03.797 --> 01:10:05.932
It ain't happening.

01:10:05.934 --> 01:10:10.235
Pick give you something,
something for you to sell.

01:10:10.237 --> 01:10:12.137
You did that?
You got my money?

01:10:12.139 --> 01:10:13.239
- I don't...
- Where's my money?

01:10:13.241 --> 01:10:14.740
I don't have it,
all right.

01:10:14.742 --> 01:10:15.978
You don't have
my money?

01:10:17.010 --> 01:10:19.212
You don't
have money?

01:10:19.214 --> 01:10:21.813
[EXHALES] Reggie,
you got two days.

01:10:21.815 --> 01:10:24.749
Two days before Pick
goes mad dog crazy,

01:10:24.751 --> 01:10:25.918
on your mama.

01:10:25.920 --> 01:10:27.954
[CHUCKLES] Ah, and your
little sweet thing over here.

01:10:27.956 --> 01:10:30.490
[CHUCKLES] 'Cause you
know he likes her.

01:10:30.492 --> 01:10:33.159
[SIGHS]
I like her, too.

01:10:33.161 --> 01:10:35.695
Now, you can forget
about your homeless hero

01:10:35.697 --> 01:10:37.565
because he's done,
he's finished.

01:10:41.536 --> 01:10:42.735
Go.

01:10:42.737 --> 01:10:43.802
[SHOUTS] Go!

01:10:43.804 --> 01:10:46.207
[MARIAH PANTING]

01:10:49.143 --> 01:10:51.046
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:11:05.626 --> 01:11:06.894
Lightning?

01:11:07.996 --> 01:11:09.965
MARIAH: Lightning!

01:11:11.131 --> 01:11:12.800
Yo, Lightning.

01:11:15.036 --> 01:11:17.706
- Reg, you don't think...
- No.

01:11:18.840 --> 01:11:19.975
All right?

01:11:22.076 --> 01:11:24.011
Theo couldn't do
nothing to Lightning.

01:11:25.979 --> 01:11:27.683
Not without some help, at least.

01:11:30.551 --> 01:11:31.920
He's gotta be
off somewhere.

01:11:34.054 --> 01:11:35.923
- This place looks abandoned,
- Stop.

01:11:36.590 --> 01:11:38.125
All right?

01:11:39.794 --> 01:11:41.596
No, Reg,
I'm scared.

01:11:42.229 --> 01:11:44.065
[SOBS]

01:11:46.267 --> 01:11:47.702
Come on.

01:11:48.769 --> 01:11:50.570
Gotta get
you home.

01:11:50.572 --> 01:11:51.873
There's another
place I know.

01:11:53.974 --> 01:11:55.341
[BELL CHIMING]

01:11:55.343 --> 01:11:57.211
[TRAIN HORN BLARING]

01:12:05.353 --> 01:12:06.822
Lightning?

01:12:09.724 --> 01:12:11.126
[EXHALES]

01:12:16.197 --> 01:12:17.833
Lightning?

01:12:21.234 --> 01:12:23.005
[EXHALING IN DESPAIR]

01:12:55.068 --> 01:12:57.203
Where have you been?
You're late.

01:12:57.205 --> 01:12:59.170
It's okay, Mom.
I'm fine.

01:12:59.172 --> 01:13:00.576
I was worried.

01:13:02.242 --> 01:13:03.308
I'm sorry.

01:13:03.310 --> 01:13:04.947
Mariah called.

01:13:05.779 --> 01:13:06.948
Did you at least
find him?

01:13:10.652 --> 01:13:13.052
Well, there's more you should
know about Lightning.

01:13:13.054 --> 01:13:15.257
Come inside, I'm gonna
show you. Come on.

01:13:18.859 --> 01:13:20.392
[YELLING]
No, no, no!

01:13:20.394 --> 01:13:22.160
- Reg...
- I know, I don't believe it.

01:13:22.162 --> 01:13:25.330
- Reggie...
- Mom, you don't think Lightning did this, do you?

01:13:25.332 --> 01:13:27.232
No, I don't.

01:13:27.234 --> 01:13:29.067
I think he's
a good man.

01:13:29.069 --> 01:13:31.036
- But...
- But? But what?

01:13:31.038 --> 01:13:32.437
It does explain
things, Reggie.

01:13:32.439 --> 01:13:33.938
Explain?
Explain what, Mom?

01:13:33.940 --> 01:13:35.074
If you don't think
Lightning did this,

01:13:35.076 --> 01:13:36.307
explain what you mean.

01:13:36.309 --> 01:13:38.110
The way he lives.

01:13:38.112 --> 01:13:39.277
What?

01:13:39.279 --> 01:13:41.981
Reggie, if he thinks
he caused this,

01:13:41.983 --> 01:13:43.883
he lives with
tremendous guilt.

01:13:43.885 --> 01:13:45.450
And if he knows
who did it,

01:13:45.452 --> 01:13:47.386
he may be
in trouble.

01:13:47.388 --> 01:13:48.987
He may have no choice
but to run.

01:13:48.989 --> 01:13:50.388
But it doesn't
sound like Lightning.

01:13:50.390 --> 01:13:51.790
It doesn't make
any sense.

01:13:51.792 --> 01:13:54.192
Reggie, I understand.

01:13:54.194 --> 01:13:56.063
But something like this
can change a person.

01:13:56.898 --> 01:13:58.431
Forever.

01:13:58.433 --> 01:14:00.335
It might be
why he's gone now.

01:14:02.437 --> 01:14:04.035
What do you mean?

01:14:04.037 --> 01:14:06.105
We're thinking about talking
to the police, right?

01:14:06.107 --> 01:14:07.306
Not about Lightning.

01:14:07.308 --> 01:14:08.740
No, not about Lightning,

01:14:08.742 --> 01:14:11.410
but we're thinking
about bringing them in.

01:14:11.412 --> 01:14:13.411
Okay. Even if we don't
say anything,

01:14:13.413 --> 01:14:16.481
someone, eventually, one day
was gonna say something.

01:14:16.483 --> 01:14:19.321
And if the police hear something
about a homeless boxer,

01:14:19.920 --> 01:14:21.222
right...

01:14:22.924 --> 01:14:24.757
So, what do we do?

01:14:24.759 --> 01:14:26.892
We take care of all this garbage
with Zeke.

01:14:26.894 --> 01:14:29.227
- Mom, what about...
- Reggie...

01:14:29.229 --> 01:14:31.896
- We can't just forget about him.
- We won't.

01:14:31.898 --> 01:14:33.834
But you know
he would want you to be safe.

01:14:35.202 --> 01:14:37.302
Let me see
what I can do.

01:14:37.304 --> 01:14:39.874
I'll go look for
him also, okay?

01:14:46.514 --> 01:14:49.451
You know, he was
quite a fighter.

01:14:51.519 --> 01:14:53.722
Top contender
for the middleweight title.

01:14:56.757 --> 01:14:58.993
- Next in line?
- Yep.

01:14:59.861 --> 01:15:01.095
Next in line.

01:15:36.029 --> 01:15:37.898
[GRUNTS]

01:15:45.105 --> 01:15:46.308
[SIGHS]

01:15:54.916 --> 01:15:56.218
[EXHALES]

01:16:22.309 --> 01:16:23.875
MAN: <i>Look at you.</i>

01:16:23.877 --> 01:16:27.346
<i>"Lightning Rod" Rhodes,
the middleweight contender,</i>

01:16:27.348 --> 01:16:29.951
<i>the best fighter
I ever worked with.</i>

01:16:31.519 --> 01:16:32.584
Paddy?

01:16:32.586 --> 01:16:36.487
Now, flat on your back
like a bum.

01:16:36.489 --> 01:16:38.324
Now, get up!

01:16:38.326 --> 01:16:41.026
- The fight ain't over.
- No, Paddy.

01:16:41.028 --> 01:16:42.994
It's over.

01:16:42.996 --> 01:16:48.933
How many times did I tell you?
It don't ever end!

01:16:48.935 --> 01:16:51.870
You pick yourself up off
the mat day after day.

01:16:51.872 --> 01:16:55.074
It doesn't matter. If the
bell rings, it doesn't matter.

01:16:55.076 --> 01:16:57.642
If they count you out,
you gotta get up.

01:16:57.644 --> 01:17:00.348
- Paddy they killed Ma.
- I know, Rod.

01:17:01.148 --> 01:17:02.513
I know.

01:17:02.515 --> 01:17:04.185
You didn't see her.

01:17:05.019 --> 01:17:06.555
You don't know.

01:17:08.488 --> 01:17:10.125
Those pricks.

01:17:11.492 --> 01:17:13.993
Those cowards.

01:17:13.995 --> 01:17:16.096
They beat her
and they left her to die.

01:17:16.529 --> 01:17:18.132
Sweet old woman.

01:17:19.532 --> 01:17:22.066
But you're still alive, kid.

01:17:22.068 --> 01:17:23.938
You still got
things to do!

01:17:26.107 --> 01:17:29.377
[SNIFFLES] I can't.
I'm done.

01:17:30.044 --> 01:17:31.477
Look at me.

01:17:31.479 --> 01:17:35.681
The boy and that woman,
they need you.

01:17:35.683 --> 01:17:37.950
And you need them.

01:17:37.952 --> 01:17:40.218
[MUTTERS]
I can't.

01:17:40.220 --> 01:17:42.186
I'll just bring 'em trouble.

01:17:42.188 --> 01:17:43.457
Get up, Rodney!

01:17:44.190 --> 01:17:45.924
- No.
- Get up!

01:17:45.926 --> 01:17:47.092
No!

01:17:47.094 --> 01:17:49.160
[YELLS]
Get up, Rodney!

01:17:49.162 --> 01:17:50.866
[SCREAMS] No!

01:17:52.099 --> 01:17:53.268
WOMAN: <i>Rodney?</i>

01:18:13.254 --> 01:18:15.122
[BELL DINGING]

01:18:17.157 --> 01:18:19.294
Come on, Rod.
I know you're here.

01:18:20.227 --> 01:18:21.630
I know you can
hear me.

01:18:26.067 --> 01:18:28.267
JOCELYN: I just
wanted to thank you

01:18:28.269 --> 01:18:30.468
for bringing my son back.

01:18:30.470 --> 01:18:32.506
I told how it was
when Will died.

01:18:35.710 --> 01:18:37.545
Reggie was devastated.

01:18:39.346 --> 01:18:40.916
Lost.

01:18:41.715 --> 01:18:43.984
Meeting you did
something for him.

01:18:45.720 --> 01:18:47.455
I don't know
why that is.

01:18:50.056 --> 01:18:52.290
I don't understand,
why you, of all people,

01:18:52.292 --> 01:18:54.426
boxing, of all things,

01:18:54.428 --> 01:18:57.265
would do that,
but thank you.

01:18:59.233 --> 01:19:01.603
He seems so alive
and happy.

01:19:03.636 --> 01:19:05.674
You might have
saved us both.

01:19:08.009 --> 01:19:12.247
Even though I have no idea
what's gonna happen.

01:19:15.382 --> 01:19:16.550
I've got some hope.

01:19:21.154 --> 01:19:22.991
Reggie told me
about this place.

01:19:25.593 --> 01:19:27.394
Said this is
where you trained.

01:19:28.496 --> 01:19:30.695
I guess this was
your world,

01:19:30.697 --> 01:19:32.099
once upon a time.

01:19:35.102 --> 01:19:37.138
I wish I would've
seen you then.

01:19:40.174 --> 01:19:42.310
I wish we both
knew you then.

01:19:45.211 --> 01:19:48.482
Rod, I know
why you disappeared.

01:19:51.385 --> 01:19:54.085
I get it.
I know the story

01:19:54.087 --> 01:19:56.291
but I don't believe it.

01:19:57.625 --> 01:19:59.160
Reggie doesn't either.

01:20:00.693 --> 01:20:03.262
You've had your problems

01:20:03.264 --> 01:20:05.632
but you're a good man.

01:20:06.332 --> 01:20:08.036
Such a good man.

01:20:09.737 --> 01:20:13.641
But, Rod, you can
only run for so long.

01:20:14.642 --> 01:20:17.375
Someday,

01:20:17.377 --> 01:20:20.447
you're gonna have to
come back and face this.

01:20:21.448 --> 01:20:22.549
If not,

01:20:24.117 --> 01:20:25.419
he'll be lost as well.

01:20:28.721 --> 01:20:30.325
Promise me,
you'll come back for Reggie.

01:20:32.492 --> 01:20:33.761
For us.

01:20:36.596 --> 01:20:37.665
For me.

01:20:40.134 --> 01:20:42.569
Promise yourself
you'll come back.

01:20:47.707 --> 01:20:49.376
Be safe,
Rodney Rhodes.

01:21:12.867 --> 01:21:15.267
[SIGHS]
Well, it's just...

01:21:15.269 --> 01:21:17.703
This is not part of an official
investigation it's just...

01:21:17.705 --> 01:21:20.472
There's just not a whole
lot I can do, I'm just...

01:21:20.474 --> 01:21:24.343
Tell my captain I have a tip
and if someone wants to talk...

01:21:24.345 --> 01:21:27.482
[SIGHS] Are you sure Zeke will
be looking for you tomorrow?

01:21:28.515 --> 01:21:30.682
Um, if not,
I can find him.

01:21:30.684 --> 01:21:32.417
I mean, he practically
lives on the street.

01:21:32.419 --> 01:21:33.619
Yeah, but you can't
talk to him on the street.

01:21:33.621 --> 01:21:34.719
It's gotta be somewhere...

01:21:34.721 --> 01:21:37.524
Somewhere where I can
overhear what's being said.

01:21:37.925 --> 01:21:39.557
Like an alley?

01:21:39.559 --> 01:21:40.859
Uh, I know one
that might work.

01:21:40.861 --> 01:21:42.628
I could bring
him to it.

01:21:42.630 --> 01:21:44.795
Nah, that's not gonna
work, it's too open.

01:21:44.797 --> 01:21:46.367
And someone could
just come on by.

01:21:46.867 --> 01:21:48.269
An empty building?

01:21:50.604 --> 01:21:51.936
That may work.

01:21:51.938 --> 01:21:55.642
As long as we can get in and
out of the place, sure why not.

01:21:56.577 --> 01:21:58.113
I have the place.

01:22:05.352 --> 01:22:07.585
Reggie?

01:22:07.587 --> 01:22:09.687
So where is
this old gym?

01:22:09.689 --> 01:22:12.292
Over on
Philbert Street.

01:22:14.327 --> 01:22:16.395
But you're
not going.

01:22:16.397 --> 01:22:17.596
I should go.

01:22:17.598 --> 01:22:20.464
No, you shouldn't be getting
involed with stuff like this.

01:22:20.466 --> 01:22:23.334
- I belong with you.
- With me. Yes.

01:22:23.336 --> 01:22:25.270
Will is my brother.

01:22:25.272 --> 01:22:26.741
Okay. Zeke is
my problem and...

01:22:27.875 --> 01:22:31.479
- What?
- And I love you.

01:22:31.745 --> 01:22:33.448
Okay?

01:22:34.648 --> 01:22:37.618
[EXHALES]
I love you.

01:22:38.986 --> 01:22:41.622
And I got you in trouble once
I don't wanna do it again.

01:22:42.822 --> 01:22:44.526
I love you, too.

01:22:46.527 --> 01:22:48.560
Please be careful.

01:22:48.562 --> 01:22:51.629
Nothing's gonna happen
Martel will be there.

01:22:51.631 --> 01:22:55.435
Hey. Martel will
be there, okay?

01:23:01.308 --> 01:23:03.342
Right.
Get out of here.

01:23:03.344 --> 01:23:06.214
When Zeke comes looking for
you, you can't run away.

01:23:07.547 --> 01:23:08.750
Go.

01:23:10.783 --> 01:23:12.319
Go.

01:23:19.827 --> 01:23:21.629
[REGGIE SIGHS]

01:23:32.505 --> 01:23:35.673
Okay, he's here.

01:23:35.675 --> 01:23:39.578
If anything happens, you call 911
immediately on my phone, okay?

01:23:39.580 --> 01:23:41.780
- I'm gonna leave it here for you.
- Okay.

01:23:41.782 --> 01:23:45.286
And do not, no matter what,
come in.

01:23:46.519 --> 01:23:48.453
[SIGHS WEARILY]

01:23:48.455 --> 01:23:51.556
I'm gonna go on in
and... And wait for them.

01:23:51.558 --> 01:23:53.292
Why don't you
get in front,

01:23:53.294 --> 01:23:54.959
help, uh... Help
Viv keep an eye out.

01:23:54.961 --> 01:23:55.996
- Okay.
- Okay?

01:24:00.634 --> 01:24:01.935
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

01:24:13.013 --> 01:24:14.515
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:24:16.317 --> 01:24:17.318
[EXHALES TEARFULLY]

01:24:21.889 --> 01:24:24.489
[THUNDERCLAP]

01:24:24.491 --> 01:24:27.528
[HIP-HOP MUSIC BLARING
FROM CAR]

01:24:36.370 --> 01:24:37.772
[WATER SPLASHING]

01:24:38.906 --> 01:24:39.971
[KEYS JANGLING]

01:24:39.973 --> 01:24:41.843
[GASPS]
Come on, Reggie.

01:24:45.946 --> 01:24:48.483
[MUSIC STOPS]

01:25:16.676 --> 01:25:17.808
[EXHALES]

01:25:17.810 --> 01:25:18.845
Wait here.

01:25:19.746 --> 01:25:21.812
Don't let anybody in.

01:25:21.814 --> 01:25:23.417
We need some privacy
for this.

01:25:26.120 --> 01:25:27.585
Reggie?

01:25:27.587 --> 01:25:28.656
Reggie?

01:25:29.489 --> 01:25:30.588
Are they coming?

01:25:30.590 --> 01:25:32.089
They're here.

01:25:32.091 --> 01:25:34.125
All right, go to your
spot, I'll be right here.

01:25:34.127 --> 01:25:35.563
Go.

01:25:47.774 --> 01:25:49.443
[SQUEAKING]

01:26:03.724 --> 01:26:06.394
[SQUEAKING CONTINUES]

01:26:19.139 --> 01:26:21.442
[SNICKERS]

01:26:26.647 --> 01:26:29.149
Is this where you hang
with your broke down homie?

01:26:30.184 --> 01:26:31.786
Where is he?

01:26:33.953 --> 01:26:35.489
Not here?

01:26:36.023 --> 01:26:37.024
Too bad.

01:26:40.461 --> 01:26:42.430
[SCOFFS AND LAUGHS]

01:26:42.962 --> 01:26:44.695
What's all this?

01:26:44.697 --> 01:26:46.597
You think I was
gonna climb in here

01:26:46.599 --> 01:26:49.534
and settle this
with you <i>mano a mano?</i>

01:26:49.536 --> 01:26:51.102
Oh, we gonna
settle it.

01:26:51.104 --> 01:26:53.204
But not that way.

01:26:53.206 --> 01:26:54.608
We ain't fighting.

01:26:57.845 --> 01:26:59.543
PICK: My money?

01:26:59.545 --> 01:27:01.615
I told you, I ain't
selling your crap.

01:27:01.849 --> 01:27:03.548
No?

01:27:03.550 --> 01:27:05.486
That's your final answer?

01:27:09.022 --> 01:27:10.591
Okay.

01:27:11.825 --> 01:27:13.627
So where is it?

01:27:15.496 --> 01:27:16.828
- Where's the goods?
- Gone.

01:27:16.830 --> 01:27:18.899
- Wrong answer!
- Doesn't matter they're still gone.

01:27:19.933 --> 01:27:23.668
My money,
or my drugs,

01:27:23.670 --> 01:27:26.771
or I'ma put you
in the cold, cold ground

01:27:26.773 --> 01:27:29.043
just like I did
your brother.

01:27:31.010 --> 01:27:32.145
Hold it right there.

01:27:36.550 --> 01:27:39.654
[BREATHES HEAVILY]
You set me up.

01:27:42.221 --> 01:27:44.623
You're dead boy.
Dead!

01:27:44.625 --> 01:27:46.790
Put the gun down.

01:27:46.792 --> 01:27:48.727
You ain't got
nothing on me.

01:27:48.729 --> 01:27:51.795
No need to have a confrontation,
nobody's going to jail,

01:27:51.797 --> 01:27:52.864
I just wanna talk.

01:27:52.866 --> 01:27:56.901
Now, put the gun down.

01:27:56.903 --> 01:27:59.937
Just talk? What you
wanna talk about, huh?

01:27:59.939 --> 01:28:01.039
Put your gun down first.

01:28:01.041 --> 01:28:02.477
You put yours down first.

01:28:08.282 --> 01:28:10.080
Okay.

01:28:10.082 --> 01:28:11.749
Let's do this together.

01:28:11.751 --> 01:28:12.918
Martel, no.

01:28:12.920 --> 01:28:14.522
Shit, I ain't gonna
shoot no cop.

01:28:17.791 --> 01:28:19.324
Not with a witness.

01:28:19.326 --> 01:28:21.929
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:28:22.729 --> 01:28:23.898
Martel!

01:28:25.098 --> 01:28:26.167
See?

01:28:26.899 --> 01:28:28.201
I'm putting it down.

01:28:33.105 --> 01:28:35.073
- Did... Did you hear that?
- [SNIFFLES] Yeah.

01:28:35.075 --> 01:28:36.874
- Call 9-1-1.
- [SOBS]

01:28:36.876 --> 01:28:39.110
[LAUGHS BOISTEROUSLY]

01:28:39.112 --> 01:28:40.281
Whoo!

01:28:42.683 --> 01:28:44.118
And now,
about that witness.

01:28:46.720 --> 01:28:48.689
RODNEY: Over here,
you worthless piece of...

01:28:58.631 --> 01:29:01.865
Oh, my God. That's...
It's Mariah, what's she...

01:29:01.867 --> 01:29:03.770
[TRAIN HORN BLARING]

01:29:11.745 --> 01:29:13.811
[SOBBING]

01:29:13.813 --> 01:29:15.879
It's not safe,
okay?

01:29:15.881 --> 01:29:17.348
Reggie's in there.

01:29:17.350 --> 01:29:19.950
Martel is with him,
you have to trust him.

01:29:19.952 --> 01:29:22.654
We have to just hope
that he's coming.

01:29:22.656 --> 01:29:23.890
Wanna play a game, punk?

01:29:24.256 --> 01:29:25.692
Sure?

01:29:26.326 --> 01:29:27.328
Here's the first move.

01:29:31.098 --> 01:29:32.597
[ZEKE GRUNTS]

01:29:32.599 --> 01:29:35.201
RODNEY: Hey, big money, what're you
packing, a Saturday night special?

01:29:36.636 --> 01:29:38.205
Enough to kill you dead,
mother...

01:29:40.373 --> 01:29:43.040
- Lightning...
- Just stay still.

01:29:43.042 --> 01:29:44.875
Where'd you come from?
What're you doing?

01:29:44.877 --> 01:29:46.947
Listen, I'm doing the same
thing Paddy would do for me.

01:29:49.349 --> 01:29:51.749
Whoa!
Lightning!

01:29:51.751 --> 01:29:52.883
Lightning!

01:29:52.885 --> 01:29:55.589
- Stay down, kid.
- Yeah, stay down, kid.

01:29:56.255 --> 01:29:59.192
Lightning, meet thunder.

01:29:59.760 --> 01:30:00.861
[GUN CLICKS]

01:30:05.331 --> 01:30:08.301
Aw. Now there's
no advantage.

01:30:09.001 --> 01:30:10.036
You sure about that?

01:30:15.375 --> 01:30:17.778
[GRUNTING]

01:30:25.719 --> 01:30:26.721
[GROANS]

01:30:34.227 --> 01:30:35.895
Argh!

01:30:46.105 --> 01:30:47.174
[GASPING]

01:30:49.108 --> 01:30:50.210
[CHOKING]

01:31:03.889 --> 01:31:05.125
He killed my brother.

01:31:07.760 --> 01:31:09.095
MAN: Bravo.

01:31:12.364 --> 01:31:13.667
Bravo.

01:31:16.368 --> 01:31:18.371
BRICK: I just
inherited a business.

01:31:19.339 --> 01:31:21.841
And I get to
kill you both.

01:31:22.075 --> 01:31:23.810
Heh.

01:31:34.987 --> 01:31:36.256
Whoa. Martel!

01:32:06.920 --> 01:32:08.887
Lightning?

01:32:08.889 --> 01:32:10.888
- Reg...
- Lightning, you can't go.

01:32:10.890 --> 01:32:12.790
I have to go.
I can't stay here.

01:32:12.792 --> 01:32:15.226
- Not now.
- Lightning, please.

01:32:15.228 --> 01:32:17.561
All right, I know
what happened, and...

01:32:17.563 --> 01:32:20.164
And no,
all right, no, no.

01:32:20.166 --> 01:32:22.566
I know. I know that
you're an innocent man,

01:32:22.568 --> 01:32:24.504
a good man.
We know you are.

01:32:25.337 --> 01:32:26.870
It's not that simple.

01:32:26.872 --> 01:32:29.807
It's... It's not what
you think it is.

01:32:29.809 --> 01:32:31.342
You can clear
your name.

01:32:31.344 --> 01:32:34.078
[CHUCKLES]
You gotta understand,

01:32:34.080 --> 01:32:35.512
it's not that.

01:32:35.514 --> 01:32:37.582
It's not the cops.

01:32:37.584 --> 01:32:40.884
It's the people that did it.
The people that killed Ma.

01:32:40.886 --> 01:32:42.920
They'll never let
the truth come out.

01:32:42.922 --> 01:32:44.489
They can't.

01:32:44.491 --> 01:32:48.959
Too many powerful people, will never
let the truth be known, remember that.

01:32:48.961 --> 01:32:51.031
Yeah, but...
But there has to be a way.

01:32:53.366 --> 01:32:54.935
No, Reg.

01:32:57.069 --> 01:33:00.174
Hey, you be strong.

01:33:02.274 --> 01:33:05.345
[POLICE SIREN BLARING
IN DISTANCE]

01:33:06.212 --> 01:33:07.281
Kid...

01:33:10.250 --> 01:33:11.986
You take care
of Jocelyn.

01:33:20.026 --> 01:33:21.228
Let me get
this straight,

01:33:22.295 --> 01:33:25.166
you were on the
ground, then what?

01:33:26.131 --> 01:33:28.600
